line: I may not look like a Murphy but I act like a Murphy.

speaker: george
line: He's extremely Murphy. He's Murphy to a fault.

speaker: jerry
line: Dublin. Originally. Parents came over here when I was eighteen. Cereal famine. Couldn't get a bowl anywhere. Bad. 'Tis a beautiful country though; lush rolling hills, and the peat, ah the peat.

line: We were right on the border.

line: Maybe he's with the company.

speaker: elaine
line: What?

speaker: kramer
line: The CIA! Maybe they placed him in there to infiltrate the organization from within.

title: The_Limo
speaker: elaine
line: What about his comedy act?

speaker: kramer
line: That's the perfect cover! All that time on the road? Look Jerry, he's too normal to be a comedian. These comedians, they're sick, neurotic people.

speaker: elaine
line: What about George?

title: The_Limo
speaker: kramer
line: What about him, he's part of it. His whole personality is a disguise. No real person can act the way he does. Elaine, I'm telling you they're with the organization. They're all part of it. He's in there with Helms and Hunt and Liddy, that whole crowd. George and Jerry, they probably know who killed Kennedy!

speaker: elaine
line: I'll bet they were even in on it.

speaker: kramer
line: Alright, what are we gonna do? I'm not gonna let him hurt you.  I'm not gonna.

line: Get off of me!!

line: Hey!

line: I wonder if I'm nuts for pursuing this woman at all.

speaker: jerry
line: Look, she slammed into a parked car! She took no responsibility for mutilating the property of a stranger, then she sped off like a criminal!

line: On the other hand, does that mean she should never be allowed to date again? You scratch one car and you're forbidden to have social contact for the rest of your life?!

line: What am I drinking, milk?

speaker: jerry
line: Oh, right, right, right, right, right, right, right, the hit and run. Well. Actually, the guy went into Queens.

line: Oh yeah. Too bad. Angela. Lousy thug. I mean what kind of sick person does something like that? That woman belongs in prison! I mean, I actually owe it to society to do something about this! I can't sit by and allow this to go on. It's a moral issue is what it is!

line: Anyway, I just wanted you to know, that I'm going to do everything I can to make sure the party responsible is made to be responsible or something very close to that.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: george
line: Well, I wouldn't want you to do that. You know there's a lot of losers out there.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: george
line: Well, that's a given.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: george
line: Must be hell living in that house.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: Hi, Michael!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: Robin? No, why?

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: No I haven't spoken to her all day-uh, yeah right, um, as a matter of fact, um, she was here, and she uh, left a note, but I wasn't here, but I have the note, uh, right here.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: Well I, I don't know.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: No, no, come on Michael!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: You're soo good lookin'.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: Let me rephra-

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: Hi Elaine, this is Angela.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: Well I think I get the gist of it.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: What car?

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: It's not complicated.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: Very nice meeting you!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: Come on up.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: Well, well, well, Mr. Seinfeld! That must have been so frightening! When you confronted that guy, in Queens! Now, let's just see if I've got this scenario right.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: Alright Elaine.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: No, no, no, no, no. Because I'm picturing 'French Connection', kind of thing. You know? Sort of a Popeye Doyle chase through the city!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: It was just a couple of blocks.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: Oh no, no, come on. Don't be so modest!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: george
line: Hey.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: Oh, did you check you machine?

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: george
line: No, why, what's happening?

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: Michael called me today, and he asked me where Robin was.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: george
line: Yeah, okay.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: And I said I hadn't seen her.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: george
line: What?!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: No, no George! You don't understand! She didn't tell me she was using me as an excuse! Okay?! But then I realized what was going on, and I said that she left a note. Um, but he didn't really buy that. And then, and then he did mention your name.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: george
line: He mentioned my name?! What did he say?!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: He said he was going to sew your ass to your face.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: george
line: What? Why couldn't you think of something?!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: Well I don't know, he caught me off guard!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: george
line: You lie! How hard is it to lie?!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: It's not that hard.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: Well who told you to sleep with her George?!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: george
line: It's not my fault! I wasn't going to do anything until you got her all juiced up with your story about having the affair with the matador!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: Oh Gosh! None of this would never have happened if you wouldn't have said 'God bless you'!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: george
line: Oh don't-

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: Hold it! Hold it! Hold it people! Matador? What matador?

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: george
line: She told this couple she had an affair with a matador.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: A matador! Well, well, well. Uno momento por favor. Pray tell, what was the young man's name?

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: elaine
line: Uh, Eduardo, uh, Carochio.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: Eduardo, Carochio! That's good. That's very good. Kind of just rolls of the tongue. I wonder where on the upper west side a single girl might meet a matador? Perhaps Zabars? Or Les Pizza!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: Anyway, this person told me to tell you to get an estimate on the damage.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: Uh, well, I'll tell you what. Um, I'll give you a check, and then this person can pay me back.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: Um, who do I make it out to?

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: So, what are you doing this weekend?

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: I didn't do it!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: You are soo good lookin'.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: You sure you want to do this? I'm going to be on the road for three weeks!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: george
line: Excuse me, I've got a maniac stalking me, I'm not staying in the city.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: Alright!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: george
line: Come on let's get out of here.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: kramer
line: How could you?

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: What?!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: kramer
line: Man! I never thought you were capable of this!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: What did I do?

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: kramer
line: I just talked to Becky Gelke outside, she told me how you hit and ran.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: I-

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: kramer
line: I don't even want to look at you anymore! All these years of friendship and you're nothing but a felon. You're an embarrassment to the building.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: I didn't do it! I just had to pay her to cover for somebody else!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: kramer
line: Now you're not going to lie to me, are you?

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: No, never.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: kramer
line: Alright. Well. Glad we got that straightened out because I've got a date with her.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: You got a date with Becky Gelke?!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah, going out with her Saturday night.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: george
line: Jerry, can we get out of here?!

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: kramer
line: As a matter of fact, if it wasn't for you, I wouldn't have even had an excuse to talk to her.

title: The_Good_Samaritan
speaker: jerry
line: Well I'm happy to help, in any way that I can.

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: You sure you don't want me to take my clothes off?  I'll do it!

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: Well, why don't you take your clothes off?

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: Well, it'd be our little secret.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Button fly! Why do they put buttons on a fly? It takes ten minutes to get these things open!

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: I like the button fly.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: What?

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: That is one place on my wardrobe I do not need sharp interlocking metal teeth. It's like a mink trap down there.  What are you doing today?

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Nothing.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: I have to go meet Nina. Want to come up to her lot, check out her paintings?

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: I don't get art.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: There's nothing to get.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Well, it always has to be explained to me, and then I have to have someone explain the explanation.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: She does a lot of abstract stuff. In fact she's painting Kramer right now.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: What for?

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: She sees something in him.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: So do I, but I wouldn't hang it on a wall.

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: Are you getting the eyes? 'Cause they're brown.  Or, really, they're dark brown, like rich, Columbian coffee.

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: She and Jerry were a big thing, like Abe Lincoln and Mary Todd.

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: Oh yeah, they're like this .

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: Why, what's the difference?

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: Well, you know... I, uh... have many relationships.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: You know, I'm a little nervous.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: Why?

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Well, you know... the friend meeting the new woman. I feel like I'm getting fixed up for a friendship.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: I don't know how long this is gonna last.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Really? I thought you liked her.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: I do... she's got like a jealousy thing. She doesn't like me having fun with anyone but her.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: You know, it's a miracle you're not married.  Hey, I'm not obligated to buy anything, am I?

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: Hi, Nina.  This is my friend George.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: Hey, look at this guy!

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah!

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: I brought George up to see some of your paintings.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Um... yeah! Sure, sure I'm interested.

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: George, you gonna buy a painting?

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Yeah, sure.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: I am an art-adorer! I adore art.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: May I?

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: What's this?

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: Oh, Saturday... I'm working, I'm going out of town.

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: They're right behind the dugout, George, first row!

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Behind the dugout, are you kidding? How did you get them?

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: All my life I've dreamed of sitting front row, behind the dugout!

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Look at where we are!  He's not stopping! He just keeps going and going and going!  We're not in the first row?

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: She said first row! Right behind the dugout!

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Well, it's the second row. It's just as good.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: I was all primed for the first row; I was gonna put my feet up on the dugout!

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Would you shut up? These are great! You can't get any better than this.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Oh, there's better,  right there, that's better.

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: Right.  Oh boy... okay, who wants a dog? What a great day!

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: I could've been at my boss' son's bris right now.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: You're supposed to do that?

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah.  What makes you think anyone would want to go to a circumcision?

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: I'd rather go to a hanging.

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Anyway, I called him back... I told him I had to go visit my father in the hospital in Maryland.

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: YOU BETTER CATCH IT,

title: The_Letter
speaker: man
line: George?

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Yeah?

title: The_Letter
speaker: man
line: Hi. I'm Leonard West, Nina's father.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Hi! Mr. West, this is my friend Elaine--

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Hi!

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: HEY, 230 AIN'T GONNA CUT IT IN THIS TOWN, BABE!

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: --and this is Kramer.

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, hey.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Okay.

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Great, great.

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Yeah, it's being framed right now. I don't even know what it costs.  Not, uh, too expensive, is it?

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah. I better!

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: You're not serious.

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Well, did he say that?

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Well maybe you should ask him!

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: No! I don't have to take it off, why should I take it off? This is ridiculous!!

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Just take the cap off.

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: George, we are at a baseball game! This is America!

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Well, I don't care, I'm not taking it off.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Just take the cap off!

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: No!

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: Hey! Just wait a minute. We just got here!

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Do you want us to go with you?

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: I'll go get your hat, George.

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Stay!

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Okay, we'll go!

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: ...and then the ball hits him in the head and he falls right over the railing!

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: Is he okay?

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Well, yeah, he's fine! We took him to the emergency room, and you know, the x-rays were all negative.  It was quite a day!

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: This is the most amazing story I've ever heard--why did he want you to take off the baseball cap? That is so insane!

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: I know! Can you imagine that?

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: How you feeling?

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, yeah, yeah, I'm fine, I'm fine.  Hey, we made the paper. Eh? Look at this- page 2, sports section... we're all in the picture.

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Wha- a picture?

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: A picture.

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: OUR PICTURE'S IN THERE??

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: Uh-huh.

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: I cannot believe this!

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: There's George!

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: Yup, yup!

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Ohmygod! Lippman could see this! He thinks I was visiting my father! Oh my g-I make up one little white lie and they put my picture in the paper!

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Hi, Mr. Lippman.

title: The_Letter
speaker: mr. lippman
line: How's your father?

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: My, my father?

title: The_Letter
speaker: mr. lippman
line: Yeah. You, you went to see him, right?

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah.

title: The_Letter
speaker: mr. lippman
line: Uh-huh.

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: I went to visit him.

title: The_Letter
speaker: mr. lippman
line: Uh-huh. So, what was wrong with him?

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Well, you name it, uh, neuritis, uh, neuralgia...

title: The_Letter
speaker: mr. lippman
line: But--but he's feeling better now?

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Um, yup. Yes, yes, it just... such a miracle, um. My visit must have buoyed  his spirits.

title: The_Letter
speaker: mr. lippman
line: Boo-eed.

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: What--what did I say?

title: The_Letter
speaker: mr. lippman
line: You said "boyed."

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: I did?

title: The_Letter
speaker: mr. lippman
line: Yeah.

title: The_Letter
speaker: mr. lippman
line: Well, I got a plane to catch.

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Oh! Where are you going?

title: The_Letter
speaker: mr. lippman
line: Going to Houston. It's a publisher's convention.  Can I have my sports section?

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Ah. ...Yeah.

title: The_Letter
speaker: mr. lippman
line: I've been saving it for the plane. I never miss the Sunday sports section.

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: There's nothing to read, it's just yesterday's news. You know, the Yankees won, the Mets lost, Ricky Henderson's unhappy...

title: The_Letter
speaker: mr. lippman
line: Right, right.  What, what are you doing?

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Wha-- oh!  Oh, god!  That is the THIRD time today I have done that! BLAAAH!  Grabbing news- papers... I'm just tugging at 'em...

title: The_Letter
speaker: mr. lippman
line: Gotta go.

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Okay! Well, you know, have a nice trip, and uh... alrighty!  I'll just hold down the, uh, fort!

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: Look, I'm really getting tired off all the fighting. Maybe we should just end this before we really start hating each other.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: Well, I like to remain friends with people I was friends with!

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Five-hundred dollars?! What?

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: That's what she told me!

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: I'm not paying $500 for this! It's a piece of junk!

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: That's what it costs!

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Why did you even take it? You broke up with her!

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: I wasn't thinking! I don't know.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: You weren't thinking.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: Well, she framed it and everything.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Well, I'm not buying it. No way. Forget it. No way I'm buying this!  I mean, look at it! What is it? It's a bunch of squiggly lines!  Are you telling me you couldn't paint this?

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: Do you want me to paint you something? I'd love to paint you some- thing!

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: I'm not paying for this. If you were going out with her, it'd be a different story.

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: This was in front of your door.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Hey, Kramer.

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: Hi, Mike.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: Wow, a letter from Nina!

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: Whoa, man! That is the ugliest thing I've ever seen!

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: Oh my god!

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: What?

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: This is amazing, you can't believe this!

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: What's it say?

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: Listen to this: "I don't know what you expect to find out there, Jerry, you know what you want better than me. But there's one thing I do know. I know I can stand here watching you destroy everything I've ever wanted in my life, wanting to smash your face with my fists, because you won't make even the slightest effort to offer happiness and still know that I love you. You mean so much to me that I'm will-ing to take all your abuse and insults and insensitivity."

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: WOW!

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: She's deep.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: "...'cause that's what you need to do to prove I'm not going to leave you. I'm sick and tired of running from places and people and relationships. You want me, that fight for me, becau-"

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: You know Jerry, she sounds like a poet!

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: No one's ever written me a letter like this. Maybe I was wrong about her!

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah! Get in there and give her a call. Pick up the phone and call her!

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: Should I?

title: The_Letter
speaker: kramer
line: YES! YOU'RE DAMN RIGHT YOU SHOULD!  Fight for her, Jerry, she's sure as hell fighting for you!

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: ALL RIGHT, all right! I'll call her.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: SHOT!  I told ya!  Yeah?

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: It's George.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: Come on up.  Well, now we gotta get a posse together. I love a good posse.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: The appeal of the posse? The posse has tremendous appeal. Get away from the job, camp out, you're with your friends... Come on, it's a week-long game of hide-and-seek on horseback.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Hey, Nina!  I owe you some money, don't I?

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Oh, yeah, me too, me too. Boy oh boy oh boy...! You know, in fact, I've been thinking about it, and I feel like I'm stealing from you! Five-hundred dollars! It's gonna be worth thousands soon! You know what? On second thought, I can't even accept it.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: This could be in a museum some day! It's not safe with me! It should really be in a doormanned building.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: Who said anything about money?

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: Yeah?

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: It's Elaine.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: Come on up.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: ...Yeah.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: She likes the pop-in. I've told her how I hate the pop-in.  He likes the pop-in, too.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: I just popped in now. I'm a big pop-in guy.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: Yeah.

title: The_Letter
speaker: george
line: How 'bout Kramer.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: HUGE pop-in guy!

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: Yeah.

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: Okay!

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Hello!

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Chatty gal.  Lippman's coming back tomorrow, I'll be fired!

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: If he noticed, he would have called you from Houston!

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: No, he wants to torture me.

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine
line: Oh! Would you gimme the clicker? I hate it when you're the clicker! You go too fast!

title: The_Letter
speaker: jerry
line: I'm a great clicker!  Great instincts. How dare you impune my clicking.

title: The_Letter
speaker: elaine

line: So I sped home to save my friend's life and I was stopped for speeding. Yes, I admit I was speeding but it was to save a man's life. A close friend. An innocent person who wanted nothing more out of life than to love, to be loved and to be a banker.

speaker: newman

So, then, he says to me, "Where do you live?" And I - and I - and I was close to your block, so I said your building. So he dropped me off in front,  and I had to take a cab all the way back downtown to my house..  Oh, God..

title: The_Outing

line: Hey, where you going?

title: The_Outing
speaker: elaine
line: I gotta go return something...

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: Thank you very much, that's great- >click< Oh! Hold on a sec, I got a call on the other line. >click click< Hello?

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Hey.

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: Hey, how ya doin'? Y'know I got that reporter from the newspaper on the other line.

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: So, what did she say?

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: She says she's not going to play up that angle of the story. She thinks we're heterosexual. [sarcastically] I guess we *fooled* her. I'll get rid of her, hold on... >click click< Sharon? Hello? Sharon, are you there? >click click< I'm back...

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Y'know... I could hear you on the other line...

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: What are you talkin' about?

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: I heard what you said: "Sharon, are you there?".

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: You heard me talkin' on the other line, are you sure?

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Yes, I heard you!

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: Well, maybe she was disconnected.

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Maybe she wasn't! Maybe she heard the whole conversation!

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: Alright, hang on. Let me call Kramer and see if you can hear anything, hold on. >click click click<...

title: The_Outing
speaker: kramer
line: Yello?

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: Kramer, there may be a problem with the phone, hold on. >click click<

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: "There may be a problem with the phone, hold on"!

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: Oh no! >click click< Kramer, this phone's a piece of junk, goodbye!

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: "The phone's a piece of junk, goodbye"!

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: Oh no! Now she's heard everything! What are we gonna do?!?

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Now she thinks we're gay, not that there's anything wrong with it...

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: No, no, of course not! People's personal sexual preferences are nobody's business but their own!

title: The_Outing
speaker: elaine
line: So she kept insisting I take off my coat. I refused, and then she forcibly tried to get me to remove it.

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: She wouldn't take her coat off at my house, either.

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Y'know there are tribes in Indonesia where if you keep your coat on in somebody's house, the families go to war!

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: So you don't take your coat off, and now everyone at NYU thinks I'm gay. Not that there's anything wrong with that...

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Not at all.

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Two tickets to "Guys And Dolls"! I'm gonna go with you!

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: "Guys And Dolls"? Isn't that a lavish, Broadway musical?

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: It's "Guys And *Dolls*", not "Guys And *Guys*".

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: "The Collected Works Of Bette Midler".

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: What do you got there?

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: "Although they maintain separate residences, the comedian and his long-time *companion* seem to be inseparable..." Oh no! The Associated Press picked up the NYU story. That's going to be in every paper! I've been "outed"! I wasn't even "in"!

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Now everyone's going to think we're gay!

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: Not that there's anything wrong with that...

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: No, not at all...

title: The_Outing
speaker: kramer
line: I thought we were friends...

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: Here we go...

title: The_Outing
speaker: kramer
line: I mean, how could you two keep this a secret from me?

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: It's not true!

title: The_Outing
speaker: kramer
line: Aaaah! Enough lying! The lying is through! C'mon, Jerry, the masquerade is over. You're thin, late thirties, single...

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: So are you...

title: The_Outing
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah--

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Hello?

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Mrs. Seinfeld?!?

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: Oh, my God! [takes the phone] Ma?

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: Ma!

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Oh, my God! My *MOTHER*!!!

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: Ma, it's not true!

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: Ma, it has nothing to do with the culottes!

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: It's *not* *true*!

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Yeah. I'm Buck Naked.

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Of course not...

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: Y'know, I think I'll pass on the "Guys And Dolls"...

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: No. Just imagine her reaction.

title: The_Outing
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah...

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Oh, my God...

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: What?

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: She hasn't seen the article! When she sees it, she's gonna think-- *I'm out baby*!! I'm out!!!!!

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Yeah so??

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Don't you see what it says here? Don't you understand what that's implying?

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: I'm gay! I'm a gay man! I'm very, very gay.

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Extraordinarily gay. Steeped in gayness.

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: You don't believe me? Ask Jerry.

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: What do you mean you will? That's a bad idea. Jerry is a very private person.

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: I dunno... [they kiss again] *Alright*, I forgive you...

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: I was attracted to you, too. You remind me of Lois Lane.

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Jerry! Oh, my God! What are you doing!?!

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: What!?

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: You're with a *woman*!

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: I know! What are you doin' here?!?

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: I leave you alone for two seconds, and this is what you do! I trusted you!

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: [forcibly removing G. from the apt] Would you get the Hell out of here!

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Alright, tell her. Go ahead.

title: The_Outing
speaker: jerry
line: Tell her what?

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Y'know. About *us*.

title: The_Outing
speaker: george
line: Alright, I'll tell you the truth. I'm not gay. My name's Buck Naked, I'm a porno actor.

title: The_Outing
speaker: kramer
line: We'll see you later...

title: The_Outing
speaker: kramer
line: He's the *phone* man!

title: The_Outing
speaker: kramer
line: Not that there's anything wrong with that...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: Oh, what's the point? When I like them, they don't like me, when they like me, I don't like them. Why can't I act with the ones I like the same way I do with the ones I don't like?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Well, you've only got another fifty years or so to go before it'll *all* be over...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: Maybe I need someone who doesn't speak English.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Yeah, how about a mute?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: A mute would be good.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Ah, where you gonna meet a mute?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: This is what my life has come to... Tryin to meet a mute.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: I dunno, Jerry somethin's missing. There's a void, Jerry, there's a void...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: A deep, yawning chasm...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: There's gotta be more to life than this. What gives you pleasure?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Listening to you. I listen to this for fifteen minutes and I'm on top of the world. Your misery is my pleasure.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Hey boys!

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Hey! How you doin'?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Good. Okay, well, it's all set. I start tomorrow.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: Start what?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: I signed up to do volunteer work with senior citizens.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: *Really*.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah. God, I can't tell you how I feel! I mean, I feel *so* *good*! I *really* feel good. The strange thing is, I mean, I haven't even met the woman yet.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: Volunteer work, huh?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: What're you gonna do down there?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Well, they say all it is is that you go over to their apartment and, I dunno, you take them for a walk and you get a cup of coffee and it's supposed to make them feel good.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: That's what I do with him [points at George]

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: When did you get this idea?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Last time I had lunch with you here. You were going *on* and *on* and *on* about how you wanted to meet somebody who didn't speak English.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: What, do you break it in with her, then you try it out on me?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: And... and anybody can do this?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Yup.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: Helping people... Of course. Of course! It makes perfect sense! How could I *not* be doing this!? I am gonna help somebody, Dammit!

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: [To Jerry] What about you?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Nah, it's not for me.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Jerry, if anybody should be doing this, it's you.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: What *kind* of a person are you?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: I think I'm pretty much like you-- only successful.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: Well, I feel better already. I'm feelin' like a good person.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Thank you.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: Hey, what's your guy's name again?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Fields. Sidney Fields. *87* years old. *87*. How about your guy?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: Ben Cantwell. 85. Huh... You think we'll make it to that age?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: *We*? No.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: So what's up, Diggity Dog?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: George and I just signed up with the Senior Citizen's Volunteer Agency. Same thing Elaine's doing.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, that's too bad. Now don't say I didn't try to warn you.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: What're you talkin' about?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, Jerry, I'm *surprised* at you!

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: What?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: It's a *con*. These agencies are usually a front for some money laundering scheme. Or they're bunko artists; bilkin' people out of their life savings, oh *yeah*.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Where do you *get* this?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: The alternative media, Jerry. That's where you hear the truth.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: newman
line: Kramer?! Kramer!? Where are you? Kramer!?! Kramer!!?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: I'm in here. C'mon...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Hello, *Newman*...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: newman
line: Jerry, George. [To Kramer] So, did you ask him about the records?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: Well--

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: What records?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: Well, Newman and I are going partners selling used records.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: newman
line: You know Ron's Records down on Bleeker? They pay big cash for used records!

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah, so we thought if you had any of those big, y'know, old-fashioned useless records, y'know, just... lyin' around--

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: Y'know, we'd take them off your hands, free of charge.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: Let me ask you something. What do you do for a living, Newman?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: newman
line: I'm a United States postal worker.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: Aren't those the guys that always go crazy and come back with a gun and shoot everybody?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: newman
line: Sometimes...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Why *is* that?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: newman
line: Because the mail never stops. It just keeps coming and coming and coming, there's never a let-up. It's relentless. Every day it piles up more and more and more! And you gotta get it out but the more you get it out the more it keeps coming in. And then the bar code reader breaks and it's *Publisher's Clearing House* day!!!

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: Five bucks???

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: newman
line: Well, you know how much those records are worth!?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: newman
line: Those records are worth more than five dollars!

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: [In Newman's ear] He's gyppin' us...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: newman
line: You're gyppin' us!

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: Wait, wait, wait... Sergio Mendes has a cult following.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: newman
line: They follow him like a cult.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: He can't even walk down the street in South America...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: [In Newman's ear] I don't like it...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: newman
line: I don't like it.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: [In Newman's ear] Alright, well be back, jack.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: newman
line: Alright, well be back... *jack*!

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Hi, I'm Jerry Seinfeld, the agency sent me.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Yeah, is this Sid Field's residence?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Mr. Fields?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Hi, I'm Jerry Seinfeld, the agency sent me.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: No, no, the--

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: The woman, she--

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Mr. Fields, I'm here to spend some time with you.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: No, Mr. Field, look, really I'm--

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: What's all this stuff?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: You're throwin' this out??

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: You don't want any of this?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: You know I have some friends who would really like to have these.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Well, do you want to go out for a walk, get a cup of coffee...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Well, maybe I'll get goin' then. I just remembered I got an appointment to get my, um, tonsils out.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: Y'know the average life span for an American male is like, 72. You're really... kinda pushin' the envelope there.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: You don't? Boy, I think about it a lot. I think about it at my age. Imagine how much I'll be thinkin' about it at your age. All I'll do is keep thinkin' about it until it drives me insane...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: Grateful? How can you be grateful when you're *so* close to the end? When you know that any second-- Poof! Bamm-O! It can all be over. I mean you're not stupid, you can read the handwriting on the wall. It's a matter of simple arithmetic, for Gods sake...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: What are you talking about? How can you sit there and look me in the eye and tell that me you're not worried?! Don't you have any *sense*?!! Don't you have a brain!? Are you so completely senile that you don't know what you're talkin about Anymore!!?!

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: Wait a second, where are you going?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: Wait a minute, please--

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Mrs. Oliver?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Ooh!

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah. Yeah. Yes. Yeah.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Did you say goiter? What goiter?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Oh, *that* goiter. Hey... Heh heh heh... Whaddya know...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Bother me? Oh, phhbt... Why would a little goiter like that bother me? No, not a bit. It's nothing. It's nothin', it's um, in fact, it's um, it's very distinctive, y'know? Um, I mean you want to know something? I, I wish I had one. [pause] Really.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: C'mon Elaine, it's just a goiter...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: I don't know what I'm going to do. I can't look the woman in the face. I mean I keep thinkin' that that goiter's gonna start talkin' to me... You'd think they'd mention that before they send you over there: "Oh, by the way, this woman *almost* has a second head". But no, no, I didn't get any goiter information.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: They really should mention that in the breakdown: height, weight, goiter.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Y'know you try to do some good. You want to be a good person but this is too much to ask.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Yeah, well, I'll tell ya, I'd rather talk to a goiter with a nice disposition than the nut they sent me to.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Hey Georgie, what happened with your guy?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: I don't think it's gonna work out...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Whattya mean?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: He fired me.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: He fired you?!?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: *How* do you get fired from a volunteer job?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: I dunno. I was just talking to the man and he walked out on me!

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Well, I dunno about you two, but I'm quitting. I hate my guy. He's a mean, mean guy.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: I wish I could quit...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: So quit!

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: Yeah, I'm a great quitter. It's one of the few things I do well. I come form a long line of quitters. My father was a quitter, my grandfather was a quitter... I was raised to give up.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: Well, here's your *albums* [Journey "Escape" is on top, BTW...]

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: What happened?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: newman
line: Five dollars. He offered us *five* dollars.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: Hey, what kind of stuff are you listening to? You *embarrassed* me at that store.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: newman
line: That guy thought we were a couple of total squares.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Oh yeah, you and your *Sergio Mendes*...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: Hey, hey, hey, hey, that guy can't even go to the bathroom in South America!

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Well you shoulda seen the pile of albums this old guy I was visiting today was throwing away: Sinatra, Duke Ellington, Al Jolson, Benny Goodman...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: Wait, wait, wait, now... He's throwin them out??

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Yeah, and then I asked him if my friend could have them and he said yeah.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: Okay...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: newman
line: [In Kramer's ear] The old coot's sittin' on a mountain of gold!

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: But you're going to have to go get em. I'm not carryin' them all.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah, but you've gotta come with us.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Yeah, I'm goin' there today. In fact you should see this house keeper he's got. She's from Senegal [and, ala Carson] Wild, Wild, Stuff...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: Senegal?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: So you don't speak *any* English at all?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Well you said they could come and take the records.

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: You don't speak *any* English?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: I would like to dip my bald head in oil and rub it all over your body. [No reaction] You don't understand! It's a miracle! You don't understand because you don't speak English!

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: So Mr. Fields I just don't know if this arrangement is--

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: Now calm down, Mr. Fields...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: kramer
line: Oooow! He's biting me!

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Where's his teeth! Where's his teeth!

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: george
line: I thought I saw something fly over here...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: Well turn the light on...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: jerry
line: That's the garbage disposal!

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Oh, well, that sounds like a lot of fun...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Uh huh...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Well, that'll get you goin' right there...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Cows, well that's fascinating...

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: What?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: Ghandhi?

title: The_Old_Man
speaker: elaine
line: You had an affair with Ghandhi? MRS. O: He used to dip his bald head in oil and rub it all over my body. Here, look... [shows Elaine a picture of the two together]

title: The_Old_Man

line: Imagine if I had to see them both on the same day?  Haha! It's like runnin' a double marathon!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: Hey Georgie, did you have any idea that anything was wrong?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Have you ever spent any time with these people...?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: george
line: You know what this has to do with?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: What?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: george
line: The man in the cape--I bet you he is mixed up in this! I don't trust men in capes.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: And you can't cast aspersions on someone just because they're wearin' a cape... Superman wore a cape... An' I'll be damned if I'm gonna stand here an' let you say something bad about him.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: george
line: All right Superman's the exception.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, hey! Elaine, I just heard that Noreen and Paul are breaking up. I want you to put in a good word for me.  I've always had a thing for Noreen.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: No, Kramer. You don't understand. This could be my fault.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: kramer
line: Well, if she's available now, I'm not gonna let her slip through my fingers this time. Nooope.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Well it looks like you've adjusted to the boxers...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: kramer
line: Wellll, I wouldn't go as far as that.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: You went back to the Jockeys?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: kramer
line: Wrong again.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Oh, no.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: What? What?...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Don't you see what's goin' on here???... No boxers, no Jockeys...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: Eeaawww...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: The only thing between him and us is a thin layer of gabardine... Kramer, say it isn't so.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, it be so. I'm out there, Jerry, an' I'm lllovin' every minute of it!!!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Don't you need a little... help?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: kramer
line: Surprisingly, no. I'm freee, I'm unfettered...  Feel like a naked innocent boy rrroamin' the countryside!!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: So you guys are tryin' to work it out! That's great!...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: Oh, he went insane?...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: Well. Uh. I don't know about sick. I mean, maybe it was somebody who, didn't wanna talk to whoever was answering because whoever was answering was always making boring chit-chat, an' was completely oblivious to the fact that the person who was calling, didn't want to speak to them, ah!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: I'm really sorry, Noreen...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: Hey, Noreen, don't go by me! Ha ha.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: What are you doin' to this woman?! This is the second relationship you've ruined for her in a few weeks!!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: I know--

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: First you ruin her relationship with the High Talker.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: Well... I got confused, they sound exactly the same.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: So she breaks up with him. Somehow picks up the pieces of her life. Miraculously meets... A New Guy! Ya bust that up! An' then, just as they're reconciling, you announce to the world: He's Boring.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: I didn't know she'd take it so seriously.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Well, apparently you have a tremendous influence over this woman: anything you say she does!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Yeah.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Come on up.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: Well, I guess I just didn't realize it...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Well, let's look back at your history with this woman. Okay?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: Okay...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: First, you encouraged her to join the army... She did.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: She was lost...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Then, you suggest she goes... AWOL! She did!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: Well, she didn't seem to be havin' so much fun...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: You know... You better make sure and never tell this woman to jump off the Brooklyn Bridge...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: If I have this much influence over her, why don't I just call her an' tell her to get back together with him--that's aalll!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Oh, Miss Changstein! This is Elaine...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: Oh.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Why? What happened?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Wow! That's amazing!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: Huh.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Tonight?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: george
line: All right.  Let me just say one thing: there is no way that this is gonna happen. You hear me? No Way! Because if you think I'm going' to two Thanksgivings, you're out of your mind!!!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: estelle
line: We're not getting divorced.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: frank
line: Your mother changed her mind...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: george
line: You did?! That's Goood! That's very good! I'm very glad to hear that.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: frank
line: Yeah, we worked it out.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: george
line: All right. So let me ask you a question. Who was the man in the cape?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: frank
line: He was my lawyer.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: george
line: Your lawyer wears a cape...?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: frank
line: Yeah. So what?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: george
line: Who wears a cape?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: frank
line: He's very independent; he doesn't follow the trends.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: estelle
line: He looks ridiculous in that thing...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: frank
line: You have no eye for fashion!!!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: estelle
line: I have no eye for fashion?!?!?!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: george
line: All right! Come on! Let's not fight.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: frank
line: All right! All right!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: estelle
line: All right! All right!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: estelle
line: Georgie's right.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: george
line: ehh.  So what made you change your mind?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: estelle
line: It was that Chinese woman.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: So I'm curious. What'd you tell Mrs. Costanza that changed her mind?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Confucius, huh?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: You know, you're not Chinese...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Hey! I heard the good news!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: frank
line: Jerry, how come you didn't say hello to me the other day, huh?!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Elaine was... in a rush.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: frank
line: I knew it was Elaine!!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: estelle
line: Yes. Who are you...?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: estelle
line: You're not Chinese!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: kramer
line: Y'ello?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: Paul?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: kramer
line: Elaine!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: Kramer?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: kramer
line: YEAHH!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: What are you doin' there?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: kramer
line: Wellll, isn't it obvious?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: Uh, is Noreen there?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: kramer
line: Yes she is...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: Well... Can I talk to her?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, what? Am I... tooo boring for you?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: Alright--would you just put her on?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: kramer
line: Well, I feel that it would be best that you didn't talk to Noreen for a while...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: YOU feel?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: kramer
line: That's right! She an' I have had a very long talk. An' I was appalled to learn of the destructive influence you've had over her life, lo these many years...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: What, are you insane?!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: kramer
line: From now on, I'll be calling the shots around here...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: Uh! Ho-ho. An' what are YOU gonna tell her?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: kramer
line: Well. I've encouraged her to go back into the Army... There she'll get the structure an' the discipline she needs right now... And she'll have qualified officers telling her what to do...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: Kramer! You have GOT to let me talk to her!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: kramer
line: Can't help ya, kid.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: Get the--

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: estelle
line: You're not Chinese!?!?

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: estelle
line: I thought you were Chinese!!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: estelle
line: Long Island?!?! I thought I was gettin' advice from a Chinese woman!!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: estelle
line: Well... then... that changes everything!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: george
line: What?!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: estelle
line: She's not Chinese; I was duped!!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: george
line: So what?! She still gave you advice; what's the difference if she's not Chinese?!?!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: estelle
line: I'm not taking advice from some girl from Long Island!!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: george
line: Wait a minute! You're--now you're getting a divorce because she's from Long Island?!?!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: frank
line: You want a divorce?!!? You got one!!!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: You know, you might wanna think about changin' your name...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: So, ever since she started dating Kramer, she won't even talk to me!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Well--Noreen listened to you like George's mother listened to the Chinese.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: You know, everybody listens to the Chinese. I mean, look at the fortune cookie. You couldn't get away with that in any other restaurant.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: elaine
line: hu_uh,  You know, everybody listens to the Chinese. I mean, look at the fortune cookie. You couldn't get away with that in any other restaurant.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Yeah, no one's reading any rolled-up messages in a knish...

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: george
line: Oh, it had to happen!!

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: jerry
line: Hey.

title: The_Chinese_Woman
speaker: george
line: I knew it!!  I predicted it!  Saw both of them today! What a disaster! I'm runnin' all over Queens. First I saw my mother. We had lunch together. Never had... LUNCH with my mother before--it's like a date! Then we drive down to Kew Gardens! Tons of traffic! I see my father. We played "Clue"! All day with this! [Kew Gardens ]

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: So, she got you to join a book club?

title: The_Couch
speaker: george
line: I got a feeling I'm gonna be much smarter than you pretty soon.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Well, I think that statement alone reflects your burgeoning intelligence.  Hey, what about this one?

title: The_Couch
speaker: george
line: Nah, I don't like that one.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: So, what's your first book?

title: The_Couch
speaker: george
line: "Breakfast At Tiffany's." 90 pages.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: It's kinda old, isn't it?

title: The_Couch
speaker: george
line: They wanted to read a Truman Capote book.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Oh, sure...Truman Capote.

title: The_Couch
speaker: george
line: He's a great writer.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Oh, yeah.

title: The_Couch
speaker: george
line: Did you ever read anything by him?

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: No. You?

title: The_Couch
speaker: george
line: Nah.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Oh, what about this one? Look at this, this is it! This is what I'm looking for.  Oh, yeah!

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Hey, what's going on?

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: New couch, baby!

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: New couch? Why?

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: I love this couch. You know what the best part about it is? It doesn't fold out, so no one can sleep over.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Hello.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Oh, let me get the door for you.  Ooh, be careful!

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Wait till you see it, it's perfect. The guy told me it's one of a kind, they stopped making it.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: What are you doing with your old couch?

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Nothing, the moving guys are taking it. Why, you want it?

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah, I'll take it.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Well, I'm sure that they can deliver it to your apartment.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Yes, they can.

title: The_Couch
speaker: kramer
line: Hey! Couch is comin.'

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: It's here!

title: The_Couch
speaker: kramer
line: Alright! Yeah. You know, I'm excited about this, Jerry. In a way, I feel like I'm getting a new couch.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Yeah. So do I.

title: The_Couch
speaker: kramer
line: Ooh! Remember Poppie?

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Oh, you mean from Poppie's Restaurant?

title: The_Couch
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah, yeah. Anyway, uh...we're going into business together. Remember that idea I had a few years ago about the pizza place where you make your own pizza?

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Yeah.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: What was that again?

title: The_Couch
speaker: kramer
line: It's a pizza place where you make your own pie! We give you the dough, the sauce, the cheese...you pound it, slap it, you flip it up into the air...you put your toppings on and you slide it into the oven! Sounds good, huh?

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Ooh, I can't wait to get me a fella and make mah own pie!

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: What made you resurrect that old idea?

title: The_Couch
speaker: kramer
line: Well, I happened to be eating at Poppie's when I told him the "old" idea, and his eyes - waaaaaah! - just lit up. You know, he wants to back it.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: I heard Poppie's was good, let's go.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: I'm not goin' there. Didn't he get busted by the Board of Health?

title: The_Couch
speaker: kramer
line: That was in the past, Jerry. As it happens, New York Magazine just judged his kitchen to be one of the cleanest in the city. They got a duck there, you think you died and went to heaven.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Ooh! I love duck. C'mon, c'mon!

title: The_Couch
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah, but you gotta order it two days in advance.  You know, I'm gonna call him, I'm gonna order the duck for you.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Oh, Kramer, I -

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Right there, guys. That's perfect. Ah? Whatta ya think, Lainie?

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Well, I don't know. I'll have to sit on it.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Oh no, I don't want anyone sitting on it.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Excuse me, I was wondering if would it be possible if you could deliver the old couch to my apartment? It's not very far.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: 'Kay. You, uh...you got room in the truck for me?

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Oh, goody. Okay, well uh......I'll see you chumps later.

title: The_Couch
speaker: kramer
line: Did you offer those guys a drink?

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Uh, no. Should I have?

title: The_Couch
speaker: kramer
line: What kind of a person are you?

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: I don't know.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: So, he puts the couch down, and just as he's about to leave he says, "Do you date moving men?"

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Ah ha...

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: You wanna know what I said?

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: I can't wait.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: "I do now."

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Clever.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Is that something?

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Yes.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Is that something?

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: You're something. So anyway, when they were in my house before, I didn't offer them anything to drink.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Well, they're real men, Jerry. They get sweaty.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: So, anyone sweaty comes into your house has to be offered a drink?

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Yes.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Well, would you apologize for me?

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Hello, Poppie. This is Elaine.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Nice to meet you, Poppie.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Well, Kramer told us all about your business venture together.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Well, your mother must be very proud of you.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: So, what's good tonight?

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Boy, I'm really looking forward to this duck. I've never had food ordered in advance before.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Ah, I could've stayed home and ordered a pizza from Paccino's.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Paccino's? Oh no. You should never order pizza from Paccino's.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Why not?

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Because, the owner contributes a lot of money to those fanatical, anti-abortion groups.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: So, you won't eat the pizza?

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: No way.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Really.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Well, what if Poppie felt the same way?

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Well, I guess I wouldn't eat here, then.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Really!

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah. That's right.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Well, perhaps we should inquire. Poppie! Oh, Poppie. Could I have a word?

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Poppie, I was just curious...where do you stand on the abortion issue?

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Oh, boy.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Well...Poppie. I think differently.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: The Supreme Court gives me the right to do that! Let's go Jerry, c'mon.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: And I am not coming back!

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Well, I'm certainly glad I brought it up.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Well, you should have seen it. It was quite a scene over there.

title: The_Couch
speaker: george
line: I'm sorry I missed it.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Oh, you really missed something. And I have to say...it was pretty much all my fault.  So, how's the book coming?  I say, how's the book comin'?

title: The_Couch
speaker: george
line: Oh...pretty good.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: So, what's it about?

title: The_Couch
speaker: george
line: Well, it's about Holly Go-Lightly.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Holly Go-Lightly.

title: The_Couch
speaker: george
line: Yeah, she's quite a character.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Yes, you haven't read a page, have you?

title: The_Couch
speaker: george
line: No.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Big surprise.

title: The_Couch
speaker: george
line: I couldn't. You know, if it's not about sports, I find it very hard to concentrate.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: You're not very bright, are you?

title: The_Couch
speaker: george
line: No, I'm not. I would like to be, but I'm not. What am I gonna do? The book club meets in a few days.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Why don't you rent the movie?

title: The_Couch
speaker: george
line: 'Why don't I rent the movie.' See, this is when I like you. Alright, now I'm relieved.

title: The_Couch
speaker: kramer
line: So...how was the dinner last night?

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: Oh...well...

title: The_Couch
speaker: kramer
line: Did you enjoy the duck?  Oh, Elaine! I was just asking how dinner went last night.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Oh...well...

title: The_Couch
speaker: kramer
line: Alright, what did you do to Poppie?

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Nothing.

title: The_Couch
speaker: kramer
line: Well, he's in the hospital. And the cook says you put him there.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: What's wrong with him?

title: The_Couch
speaker: kramer
line: I don't know! I'm gonna go and visit him later.  It would be nice if you got him something.

title: The_Couch
speaker: jerry
line: We should get him something.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah. You're right.

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: Do you know that I have been using the same bottle of shampoo for a year? And I shampoo every day.  So, what do you think of my conversation?

title: The_Couch
speaker: elaine
line: You don't have any furniture?
