Yeah, hi, it's Jerry Seinfeld, remember those tickets I gave you?  Well it turns out I can use them.  Oh, you do?  I understand.  Okay.  Bye.  He already made plans, he can't change them.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: Well they're his tickets, he can do what he wants with them.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Thanks.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: Alright, I gotta go.  I'm heading over to Bonnie's.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: What are you gonna do about the roommate?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: I gotta try and find a way to switch places with him.  It's like a Sigfried and Roy trick.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Well, the pickle breath is a good start.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: newman
line: Hello Jerry, may I come in?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: What do you want?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: newman
line: Nothing, just being neighborly.  Do you wanna hang out?  Shoot the breeze?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: I'm not letting you cheat, Newman.  You're not getting anywhere near that board.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: newman
line: Jerry?  I'm a little insulted.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: You're not a little anything, Newman.  So just pack it up and move it out of here.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: newman
line: Oh, by the way, what are you doing for the Super Bowl?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: I dunno, watch it on TV I guess.  Why?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: newman
line: Well if you watch closely enough, you just might see me.  I'll be the one waving to the camera from my seat on the forty yard line.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: You're going to the Super Bowl?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: newman
line: Yes I am, a guy on my mail route just got a couple of tickets and he offered one to me.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: What's his name?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: newman
line: Tim Whatley.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: That's my ticket!

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: newman
line: Is it?!  Ohhh, well if only you'd known, you could have saved some time and given it directly to me!  Ha ha ha.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Newman!

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: What a movie.  Good choice.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: Oh, Scott, Scott.  He's really great, isn't he?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: Yes he is.  Let me ask you something.  When you come out of the shower and you put your robe on, do you cinch it real tight, are you concerned about that?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: Do you hold the neck together with one hand, or are you just letting it flap in the breeze?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: What's the massage situation?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: Is there any work being done?  Is there any rubbing, touching, finger manipulation on the other person, and if so, who's making the request?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: Say you go to the bathroom at two o'clock in the morning, what's the outfit?  I mean, you dressing up or is it come as you are?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: I'll tell you what's wrong, a grown woman with a male roommate!  It's unnatural, it's an abomination!

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: Hey!

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: I'm good.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: Yes it is.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: Aren't you gonna invite me upstairs?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: I would love to go upstairs.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: We'll see.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Newman.  He's going with Newman.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: How does Tim Whatley even know Newman?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Newman's his mailman.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: Who goes to the Super Bowl with their mailman?!

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Who goes *anywhere* with Newman?!

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: Well, he's merry.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: He is merry, I'll give him that.   What's this plant for?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: I had a little tiff with Bonnie about the roommate.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Oh, well the cactus will smooth things over.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: Hey, guess what?  I'm going to the Super Bowl with Tim Whatley.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: What?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: We went out for coffee last night and he offered me a ticket.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: What about the label maker?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: Ah, well.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Wait a minute, that's my ticket!  You didn't even want to go.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: It was totally out of the blue.  We went upstairs to his apartment, you know, to look for the label maker.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: So, how did you get up there?  Did you say you had to use the bathroom?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: No.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Then how'd you get up there?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: I said, "Do you wanna go upstairs?"

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: And there's you ticket.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: What?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: That's why you're going to the Super Bowl.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: Why?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: You go out with a guy one time, you ask him to go upstairs like you're Mae West?  Of course he's gonna try and get you alone for the weekend.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: You mean just because I asked him to go upstairs, he thinks he's going downtown?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Obviously.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: You're crazy.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: Well, what happened when you got upstairs?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: As soon as we walked in, he got a call from one of his patients with an impacted molar or something so he had to leave.  I didn't even get a chance to look for the label maker.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Yeah, well I don't trust this guy.  I think he regifted, he degifted, and now he's using an upstairs invite as a springboard to a Super Bowl sex romp.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: kramer
line: Hey.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Hey.  What are you doing?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: kramer
line: I'm watching your door.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: My door?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah, from my peephole.  Fisheye, sees all.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: What was that?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: kramer
line: Newman!

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: newman
line: Damn!

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: The bedroom!

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: I see you, Newman!  I see you!

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: kramer
line: I'm taking the Congo as a penalty!

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: I've got a confession to make.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: I've got Super Bowl fever.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: So where are we staying?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: Oh.  Big room?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: Downtown?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: What do they have there, a couple of beds?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: No, but don't you think there should be two beds?  There's two of us.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: So she kicked him out of the apartment.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: That's right.  It's just me and her.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Wow, she rearranged her whole life for you.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: I guess she did.  He's gone, now I'm the man.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: That's not a good role for you.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: No, it's not.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: You unwittingly made a major commitment.  That's a lot of pressure.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: Oh my god.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: You wanted to be ensconced in velvet, you're buried.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: I had the perfect situation here, he was shouldering half the load.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: He was shouldering.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: I couldn't leave well enough alone?!

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Where are you going?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: I gotta go help her tape up all his boxes and get them ready for shipping.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Oh, well here.  Take Whatley's label maker, I don't want to see it again.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: Thanks.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah.  I am taking over South America and there ain't nothing you can do about it.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: So, too bad about that Super Bowl ticket, eh Newman?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: newman
line: Yeah.  I just hope Tim Whatley's electric bills don't suddenly get lost in the mail, or it could be lights out for him.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Thanks for having me over, guys.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Alright, I'll see you later.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Ah, Tim Whatley.  Out scalping?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Are you serious, what about Elaine?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Oh.    Hey, isn't this Kramer's car?   Hey, Cosmo!!  They're towing your car!!

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: kramer
line: What?!  Not my car!!  Hey!!  They're towing my car!!

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: newman
line: What are you doing?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: kramer
line: I'm taking the board with me.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: What, what happened?  Where's, where's all the stuff?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: The table, the stereo, the VCR, the velvet couch, where's the velvet?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: newman
line: Are you sure you know where the impound yard is?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, stop stalling.  Come on.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: newman
line: I can't think, there's all this noise.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: kramer
line: Or is it because I've built a stronghold around Greenland?  I've driven you out of Western Europe and I've left you teetering on the brink of complete annihilation.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: newman
line: I'm not beaten yet.  I still have armies in the Ukraine.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: kramer
line: Ha ha, the Ukraine.  Do you know what the Ukraine is?  It's a sitting duck.  A road apple, Newman.  The Ukraine is weak.  It's feeble.  I think it's time to put the hurt on the Ukraine.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah, well we're playing a game here, pal.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: Hello, Tim.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: Don't worry, Tim.  I didn't come by to yell at you, I didn't come by for that at all.  I just came by to pick up my label maker.  I gave you a label maker and now I would like to have it back.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: But you gave me a ticket to the Super Bowl.  Hand it over, Whatley.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: You don't have the label maker, do you?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: I knew it!  You're a regifter!

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: What?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: elaine
line: Well, I bought it for you because you were so nice to me for not charging me for the dental work.  The way you worked on my filling, you were so, so gentle and so caring and so sensitive.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: H... G... F.  Seat four.  One, two, three... f-- Hello Newman.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: newman
line: Hello, Jerry.  Tim couldn't make it, he's in love.  Isn't that wonderful?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Oh, it's enchanting.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: Here's the TV.  I know you wanted to watch the Super Bowl.  Do you at least have some towels we could sit on?  It's, like, a four hour game.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: How am I gonna get out of this?  Think Costanza, think!

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: Hey, do you know, Bonnie, I just had a pretty wild idea.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: george
line: Well I, uh, I'm not sure how you pronounce it or anything, but I, uh, I believe it's Ménage à Trois?

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: newman
line: Great streak of luck I'm having.  First, Kramer almost beat me at Risk but I narrowly escaped, and then Tim Whatley gives me his Super Bowl ticket.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: Can you move over at all?!

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: newman
line: And then, just as I'm about to go, these boxes show up at the post office with no labels.  No labels, Jerry.  You know what that means?  Freebies!! I got this great mini-TV and a VCR, oh it's unbelievable.

title: The_Label_Maker
speaker: jerry
line: An inch!  Can you move over an inch?!?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Gary? Well, well, well well. Where the hell've you been? I've been leaving you phone messages for months.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Busy. Don't give me busy. Who's not busy? I'm busy, we're all busy, everybody's busy. All right, tell me, what's kept you so busy?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: So you called the cop a pig?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: I was yelling at the litterbug. I mean this is my town. You don't throw trash on the streets of my town.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: Didn't you explain that to the cop?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: No, I fled the scene.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: Hey.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: Hey buddy.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Hey, uh...

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: What?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Kramer, I, I, I, uh, I need to talk to Jerry privately.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: Oh. What about?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Kramer...

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: Aw come on George, you can share it with me, huh?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Hey, you're hurting me!

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: You gonna share it with me next time, huh?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: I swear, I swear!

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: Aw, all right, I'm looking forward to it.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Right, I got news. You ready?  Gary Fogel had cancer.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: Oh yeah, I knew.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: You knew? How did you know?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: He told me a few months ago.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Why did he tell you and not me?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: I don't know.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: How are you closer to him than me?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: So, is he okay?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: Oh yeah, he's fine, fine. He was in bad shape for a while though.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Huh, really? How bad? Was he on his death bed?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: No, he was on his regular bed.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: So why didn't you tell me?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: He swore me to secrecy.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: So?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: It's not like you're my wife.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Well, I still think you shoulda told me.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: Hey, believe me, you were better off not knowing. It's not easy to deal with someone in a situation like this. I was so nice to him I almost made myself sick.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Well, I wanna talk to him about this.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: That's right, you let him have it.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Mmm-mm.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: Who is he not to tell you about his life-threatening illness?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: That's what I'm saying.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: His illness is your business.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: If not mine, whose?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: If not now, when?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: elaine
line: Were you just talking about me?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: No, an old friend of ours, Gary.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: elaine
line: Oh, the guy with cancer?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: You told her? She's not your wife!

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: If I told you, you woulda given it away.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: You don't think I can keep a secret?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: No, but he would've read your face.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: You don't trust my poker face?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: Do you ever win at poker?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: No.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: Hey.  Oh, I just saw your old boyfriend on TV.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: elaine
line: Egh, Jake Jarmel?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah. I really liked those glasses he was wearing. Where'd he get those.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: elaine
line: Why? You don't wear glasses.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: I know, I know. But I need a new look, I'm stagnating.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: I have to say, as a glasses wearer I take exception to that. That's like me buying a wheelchair to cruise around in.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah, I've considered that.  Look, how do I get in touch with this guy?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: elaine
line: Well, he's having a two day book signing at Waldens.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: Ah.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: elaine
line: You know, we had a really bad break-up.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: The Jujy Fruits?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah, the Jujy Fruits.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: Okay, thank you. Listen Jake, uh, where did you get those eyeglass frames?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: So you don't know where you got 'em?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: Well, that's peculiar.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Eh, there's that woman that never talks to anybody.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Every day she comes in, she sits at that table and reads. Never talks to anybody.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Really?  You know Gary, I really have to say, I'm a little bit hurt that you didn't decide to confide in me.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Well I still think it was wrong.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Yes.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: ...so I called the litterbug a pig, not you. I like policeman. I wanted to be a policeman.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: Scared of being shot.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: I like that eye patch.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: All right, I'm gonna move my car, my meter's up. Can't park in this city.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Wha, that's a Kinney lot?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Fifty bucks a month, that's incredible! Okay, thanks.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: You still owe me a secret.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Yeah?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: What do think I tell Jerry everything? It's not like he's my wife.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: george
line: Just one? I'm living like twenty.  What's yours?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: elaine
line: So he refused to tell you where he got the glasses?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: Flat out refused!

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah, isn't that just like him?  You know, he has to be the only one who has 'em.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah, tell me about it, soul sister.  Anyway, I told Jake that you said hi.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: elaine
line: What?  You told Jake I said hi?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: elaine
line: I can't believe you did that! Why did you tell him I said hi? I never said hi!  When did I say hi?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: I never heard her say hi.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: kramer
line: Well, it's uh, common courtesy.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: elaine
line: No, no.  Kramer, you don't understand. He made the last contact between us. I had the upper hand in the post-breakup relationship. If he thinks that I said hi, then I lose the upper hand.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: It's like a game of tag.

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: jerry
line: Where you going?

title: The_Scofflaw
speaker: elaine
line: Nowhere.

title: The_Scofflaw

line: Before we go any further, I'd just like to point out how disturbing it is that you equate eating a block of cheese with some sort of bachelor paradise.

line: Don't you see? I'm back in.

line: Yes!

line: Well, it was the best of those movies.

line: KHAN!

line: Oh!

line: Oh. I know they have some monies.

line: So, if Susan and I had... I mean, if the envelopes hadn't, uh... then we--

title: The_Foundation

line: And now?

speaker: george

line: Well, that's the thing. It was completely mutual.

title: The_Foundation

line: I am. It was the world's first.

line: Well, I can't argue with that, but the fact remains... I was completely...  Mulva!

line: Hello?

line: Hey. Guess who just finished laying out her first issue of the J. Peterman Catalog.

line: How's it look?

speaker: elaine
line: It's a peach.

speaker: jerry
line: Huh?

speaker: elaine
line: I say, it's a peach.

speaker: jerry
line: Elaine, let me ask you something. When I told you my breakup was mutual, did you believe me?

title: The_Foundation
speaker: elaine
line: No, no, no. It's weak. No one's gonna buy it, and you shouldn't be selling it.

title: The_Foundation
speaker: jerry
line: I gotta do some research here.

title: The_Foundation
speaker: elaine
line: Hey, hey. Me. Talking. You know, between you and me, I always thought Kramer was a bit of a doofus, but he believed in me. *You* did not. So as I see it, he's not the doofus. *You* are the doofus.

title: The_Foundation
speaker: jerry
line: Oh, I'm the doofus?

title: The_Foundation
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah. You, Jerry, are the doofus.

title: The_Foundation
speaker: jerry
line: You know, it occurs to me that Kramer is at karate right now.

title: The_Foundation
speaker: elaine
line: Oh, well, maybe I'll just go down there and thank him in person.

title: The_Foundation
speaker: jerry
line: Yeah, that's what I was thinking.

title: The_Foundation
speaker: elaine
line: Kramer!

title: The_Foundation
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, hey.

title: The_Foundation
speaker: elaine
line: What are you doing?

title: The_Foundation
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, well, I-I-I'm dominating.

title: The_Foundation
speaker: elaine
line: You never said you were fighting children.

title: The_Foundation
speaker: kramer
line: Well, it's not the size of the opponent, Elaine, it's, uh, the ferocity.

speaker: elaine
line: This is what you used to build me up? This is where you got all that stupid katra stuff?

title: The_Foundation
speaker: kramer
line: No, no. That's from, uh, Star Trek III... The Search for Spock.

title: The_Foundation
speaker: elaine
line: Search... for Spock?!

title: The_Foundation
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah, I know Jerry will tell you that The Wrath of Khan is the better picture, but for me, I always...

title: The_Foundation
speaker: elaine
line: You doofus!

speaker: kramer
line: I thought you said your mom was meeting us in the alley.

title: The_Foundation
speaker: kramer
line: What's going on? Hey, Timmy, Clara. That was some kind of workout we had tonight, huh?

title: The_Foundation
speaker: kramer
line: Aah! Aah! Mama!

speaker: jerry
line: So... did you stop by the dojo?

line: Yep.

speaker: jerry
line: How's your confidence level?

speaker: jerry
line: Self-esteem?

speaker: elaine
line: Gone.

speaker: jerry
line: Doofus?

title: The_Foundation
speaker: elaine
line: Yo.

speaker: jerry
line: All right, so what? You put out the catalog. How bad could it be?

speaker: jerry
line: What is that?

speaker: elaine
line: It's the Urban Sombrero. I put it on the cover.

speaker: jerry
line: Well, nobody sees the... cover.

speaker: kramer
line: God!

title: The_Foundation
speaker: jerry
line: What happened to you?

title: The_Foundation
speaker: kramer
line: Whew! I got whooped. You should have seen the rage in their little eyes. And those tiny little fists of fury. Oh.  What is that?

title: The_Foundation
speaker: jerry
line: It's the new cover of the J. Peterman Catalog. It is Elaine's choice. Let's congratulate her.

title: The_Foundation
speaker: kramer
line: Oh I see.  Woof!

title: The_Foundation
speaker: elaine
line: You! This is all your fault! You told me I could run the company!

speaker: kramer
line: Well, then I was way off!

title: The_Foundation
speaker: elaine
line: Well, I'll see ya...

title: The_Foundation
speaker: jerry
line: Vaya con dios.

title: The_Foundation
speaker: kramer
line: Man, I gotta go lay down. You and George going out a little later?

speaker: jerry
line: No, he's still stuck at the foundation.

speaker: kramer
line: You know, you oughta go down there and help him out. He's a widower.

speaker: jerry
line: Widower? Wait a second.

speaker: george
line: Would I have had access to that?

line: And now?

line: Not.

line: Hello?

speaker: jerry
line: Hey, Georgie! I'm doing some research down at the coffee shop. Your story's the one.

line: My story?

line: Yeah, your widower story's tested through the roof.  When are you getting out of there?

line: Uh, excuse me, Wyck. Uh, are we, uh, almost done here?

line: I can't go.

speaker: jerry
line: What do you mean you can't go? There's two really girls sitting at the counter eating grilled cheese. Cheese, George! Cheese!

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: You want me to find a poem about Susan? May she rest in peace?!

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: I like, uh...

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: He cleared his throat?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: Yes!

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: So?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: He did it right as he said "her unfortunate accident."

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: Not getting it.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: Jerry, a throat-clear is a non-verbal implication of doubt - he thinks I killed Susan!

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: Oh, help me, Rhonda.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: What time is it?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: Right now?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: I gotta go meet Pam.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: Oh, the bookstore girl. How's that goin'?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: Okay. I'm just not ga-ga over her. For once I'd like to be ga-ga.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: Where's Elaine?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: She's having Carol, Gail and Lisa over. You know they all have kids now?

speaker: george
line: What's with all these people having babies?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: Perpetuation of the species.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: Yeah! Right!

speaker: jerry
line: By the way, just for the record -

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: No, I did not!

speaker: elaine
line: Well, that's...that's sweet.

speaker: elaine
line: Oh, hey, you know...I had a piece of whitefish over at Barney Greengrass the other day...

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: I really like the city.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: Uh, it was in the Hamptons.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: No, no, that's okay, it's uh...

speaker: jerry
line: So, Elaine was telling me about this piece of whitefish she had the other day...

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: Do you really think I'm wrong about this Wyck guy?

speaker: jerry
line: You know, if you really want to test him out, why don't you try the old Jerry Lewis trick?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: Jerry Lewis?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: I heard that when Jerry Lewis left a meeting, he'd purposefully leave a briefcase with a tape recorder in it. Then after five minutes, he'd come back for it and listen to what everyone said about him.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: That's pretty paranoid.

speaker: jerry
line: Yes, it is.

title: The_Soul_Mate

line: I like it!

line: I thought you might.

line: Books.

speaker: jerry
line: Hi, sorry I'm late.

speaker: jerry
line: You know, if we rush, we can still make the movie.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: I'm in trouble, buddy. I just met a woman.

speaker: newman
line: Go on.

speaker: kramer
line: Well, she's Jerry's girlfriend.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: newman
line: Ah, yes. Forbidden love.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: She works in a book shop. Her name is Pam.

speaker: newman
line: "Pam." I don't know the woman, but she sounds quite fetching.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: I can't even speak in front of her.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: newman
line: Jerry! What could she possibly see in Jerry?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: She has delicate beauty.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: newman
line: Jerry wouldn't know delicate beauty if it bludgeoned him over the head.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: And yet, he's my friend.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: newman
line: And therein lies the tragedy. For I believe, sadly for you, that there is but one woman meant for each of us. One perfect angel for whom we are put on this earth.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Aw, that's beautiful, Newman.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: newman
line: One winsome tulip we ceaselessly yearn for throughout our dreary, workaday lives! And you, my friend, have found your angel. I can tell. For my heart has also been captured by a breathless beauty - whom I fear I will never possess.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: I thought we were talking about me.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: newman
line: Right. Kramer, you have to confront Jerry.

speaker: kramer
line: Confront Jerry? I can't.

speaker: newman

speaker: kramer
line: I won't!

speaker: newman
line: You will!

speaker: elaine
line: "Elaine, ya gotta have a baby." Ugh.

speaker: george
line: Where are all the poetry magazines?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: The New Yorker has poetry.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: Yes. The New Yorker.

speaker: jerry
line: Why do you invite these women over if they annoy you so much?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: They're my friends, but they act as if having a baby takes some kind of talent.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: C'mon, you want to have a baby.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: Why? Because I can?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: It's the life force. I saw a show on the mollusk last night. Elaine, the mollusk travels from Alaska to Chile just for a shot at another mollusk. You think you're any better?

speaker: elaine
line: Yes! I think I am better than the mollusk!

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: Oh, I'm sorry.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah, like you must procreate.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: Oh, it's been done to death.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: I, uh, should have a poem very soon now.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: No, no, not really. Ever since Susan passed on, I have good days and bad.  Some days, I'm haunted by one word - why. Why Susan? Why wasn't it me licking those invitations? Why am I still here? Well, I gotta run.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: Briefcase.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: So, Kevin. If I don't want children, does that make me a bad humanitarian?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: 'Cause, I mean, when you get to know me, you'll see that I'm a pretty good humanitarian.  You are doing a wonderful job, by the way. Thanks a lot.  Right? Am I right?  Kramer. Kramer! Come here, look at my new friend Kevin.  Oh, you got a little, uh...

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, I just had two double-fudge sundaes.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: Oh. Are you alright?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah, I'll be okay.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: You know, Jerry has one of those every time he bombs on stage.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Well, I'm sure he'll be sharing his next one with Pam.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: Oh, no...that won't last.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: What do you mean?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: He's not ga-ga.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: Lemme tell you something, that Jerry Lewis? You wonder how some of these people get to the top? It's ideas like this! Brilliant! Hah-hah!  Look at this - what the hell happened? The whole side is damaged here...and the lock is broken.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: How long did you leave it up there?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: Five minutes. What the hell happened here?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: Play the tape, maybe we'll get a clue.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: I have to rewind it first.  Alright, alright.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: Is that it?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: Stopped dead.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: What do you make of it?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: I don't know.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Jerry. Uh, can we talk?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: Kinda busy here.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: I'd like to talk to Jerry in private.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: Why can't I stay?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Because it doesn't concern you.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: Well, if it doesn't concern me, then I can stay.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: So, what's on your mind?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: It's Pam.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: Pam? What about Pam?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: I love her, Jerry!

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: You what?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: I love her!

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: Is that right?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, she's uh...she's real. She can bring home the bacon and fry it in the pan.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: What does that mean?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, and that voice!

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: What about her name?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Pam? Oh, it's a beautiful name.  Pam. Pam. Pam!

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: She's got really nice hair.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, it's incredible. Although, I might replace her tortoise clip with one of those velvet scrunchies. I love those.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: You've got really specific tastes.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, I know what I want, Jerry.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: She's got nice calves.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, she's a dreamboat. But, you don't like her, so...

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: Maybe I could, you're making some pretty good points.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: No you can't, Jerry.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: But I might.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, no you don't.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: Why not? The voice? The calves? The bacon?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: What...?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: I think I can! I even like the name! Pam!

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Huh?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: Pam!

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Huh?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: Pam!

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Huh-yah!

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: So now he wants her more than ever!

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: newman
line: Blast!

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: What am I gonna do, huh?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: newman
line: Don't despair, my friend.  I won't allow your love to go unrequited. Not like mine.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: What, again with you?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: newman
line: Sorry. But love is spice with many tastes. A dizzying array of textures...and moments.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: If only I could say things like that around her.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: newman
line: Yes...

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: Well, I hear three distinct sounds. A low rumple...followed by a metallic 'squink'...

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: Yes! Yes, I heard the 'squink'!

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: ...followed by a mysterious...'glonk.'

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: It's baffling, isn't it?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: Well, one question does come to mind. Have you considered just...asking them what happened to the briefcase?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: They would never tell me, Elaine. First of all, they probably think that I killed Susan. Besides, I don't even think they like me.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: That Pam! I am ga-ga over her!

speaker: elaine
line: Ga-ga? When did that happen?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: Yesterday. Six-ish.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: Well, maybe we should double. I'm pretty ga-ga myself.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: You just met the guy yesterday.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah, but we have a common goal.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: A barren, sterile existence that ends when you die?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: And you really believe this guy doesn't want to have kids.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah, of course.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: Elaine, a guy'll say anything to get a woman.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: elaine
line: Oh, please. He wouldn't say that.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: Elaine, I once told a woman that I coined the phrase, "Pardon my French."

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: jerry
line: I once told a woman that I don't eat cake 'cause it goes right to my thighs.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: george
line: I once told a woman that I really enjoy spending time with my family.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: newman
line: With your looks and my words, we'll have built the perfect beast.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: newman
line: Hi. How are you?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Hi. How are you?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: newman
line: I too am well.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: I too am well.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: newman
line: Do I smell Pantene?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Do I smell?

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: newman
line: Pantene!

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Uh, Pantene.

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Well, there really is no junk-mail...well, everybody wants to get a check or a birthday card, but...

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: newman
line: ...it takes just as much man-power to deliver it as their precious little greeting cards...

title: The_Soul_Mate
speaker: kramer
line: Newman!

line: Eh, I can't. I gotta go down to the foundation. I'm interviewing high schoolers for the Susan Ross.. scholarship.

speaker: george
line: Woah, woah, woah! What are you telling me for? You really had me going, there! C'mon, sit down.  What do you want to do when you grow up?

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: elaine
line: So, get this: Mister Peterman is finally letting me do some real writing. He's got this book deal, for his autobiography. He's gonna let me ghost write it.

speaker: jerry
line: Wow. That's great! When it comes out, I'll have to get someone to ghost read it.

speaker: kramer
line: Hey.

speaker: jerry
line: Hey.

speaker: elaine
line: Hey!

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: Alright, so there I am at Lorenzo's - loading up my slice of the fixin's bar.. garlic,  and what-not.. mmm, mmm.. and I see this guy over at the pizza boxes giving me the stink-eye.  So I give hime the crook-eye back,  you know.. Then, I notice that he's not alone! I'm taking on the entire Van Buren Boys!

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: jerry
line: The Van Buren Boys? There's a street gang named after President Martin Van Buren?

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: Oh yeah, and they're just as mean as he was! So, I make a move to the door, you know,  they block it! So, I lunged for the bathroom.  I grab the knob - Occupado! Then they back me up agains the cartoon map of Italy, and all of the sudden, they just stop.

speaker: elaine
line: What? What happened?

speaker: kramer
line: Because I'm still holding the garlic shaker.. Yeah.. like this  I'm only showing eight fingers.

speaker: jerry

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: That's their secret sign! See, Van Buren, he was teh eighth President..  They thought I was a former Van B. Boy!

speaker: jerry
line: She coming of a bad break-up?

speaker: jerry
line: Any messages?

speaker: jerry
line: They act like it was some act of charity. Just going out with her.

speaker: george
line: So, she's the loser of the group. Every group has someone that they all make fun of.. Like us with Elaine.

speaker: jerry

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: george
line: Hey, I htink I may have found someone for the scholarship.

speaker: jerry
line: Yeah?

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: george
line: I'm interviewing all these annoying little overachievers.. finally, this kid walks in - Steven Koren - a regular guy.. likes sports.. watches T.V..

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: jerry
line: Is he smart?

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: george
line: He knows how to read. And he also knows finishing an entire book doesn't prove anything. And get this: he's into architecture.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: jerry
line: Hey! Just like you pretend to be.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: george
line: Yes. With a little guidance, Steven Koren is going to be everything I claim to be, only for real. That's my dream, Jerry.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: jerry
line: I had a dream last night that a hamburger was eating me!

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: elaine
line: Mister Peterman, thanks for having me over. Your place isn't quite what I imagined..

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: peterman
line: Ohhh.. It's just a place to flop.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: elaine
line: Well,  what part of your life  do you want to start with? Foreign intrigue? Exotic romances?

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: peterman
line: Oh, Elaine, we've covered all of that in the catalogue ad nauseum. No, I would like this book to be about my day-to-day life.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: elaine
line: Oh.

speaker: peterman
line: Oh damn. They changed the cable stations again.. just when I finally memorized them.

speaker: elaine
line: Well, Mister Peterman, do you want to, um..

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: elaine
line: get, um, started..

speaker: peterman
line: 3.. I don't know what that is.. where's my damn preview channel?

speaker: elaine
line: Well, I - I got ta tell you, Mister Peterman.. I don't think I see a whole book here.

speaker: peterman
line: well, I'm sure we'll come up with something. What do you say you and I order ourselves a pie? Do you like Lorenzo's?

speaker: elaine
line: You know, a friend of mine almost got beat up at that place by the Van Buren Boys?

speaker: peterman
line: You don't say.

speaker: elaine
line: Yeah. The only think that saved him is that he accidentally flashed their secret gang sign.

speaker: peterman
line: Well, that's pretty exciting.  Let's put that in the book.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: elaine
line: But, that didn't happen to you.

speaker: peterman
line: So, we pay off your friend, and it becomes a Peterman.

speaker: elaine
line: No, I - I really don't think you can do that.

speaker: peterman
line: Ohh, damn. I forgot to buy plant food again.. I'll bet I got a coupon for it.

speaker: elaine
line: You know what? Maybe I better talk to my friend.

speaker: jerry
line: Is that the same outfit you were wearing yesterday?

speaker: jerry
line: Actually, yeah.  Wait a second! Is that the fork that fell on the floor?!  Are you using the fork that fell on the floor?!

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: jerry
line: I guess that's all right.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: jerry
line: No, absolutely nothing.  You're fantastic!  Hey guys!

speaker: george
line: Hey.

speaker: jerry
line: Kramer, George, this is Ellen.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: george
line: Ladies and gentlemen, this  is Steven Koren. His G.P.A. is a solid 2.0! Right in that meaty part of the curve - not showing off, not falling behind.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: george
line: I'm sure we're all aware of the flaws and biases of standardized tests..

speaker: george
line: Besides, Steven Koren has the highest of aspirations. He wants to be  an architect.

speaker: george
line: Steven, nothing is higher than an architect.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: george
line: No, it's not.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: george
line: It's called a T-square.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: And they made it their sign, because, Van Buren, our 8th President, was the man they most admired.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: peterman
line: Kramer, my friend, that is one ripping good yarn..

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: You know, if you like that one, I got more.. what are you looking for? Romance? Comedy? Adventue? .. Erotica?

speaker: elaine
line: No, uh, Kramer. I don't think -

speaker: peterman
line: How much would you take for the whole lot?

speaker: kramer
line: My whole lot?

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: peterman
line: Name your price, man!

speaker: kramer
line: 1500 dollars.

speaker: peterman
line: I'll give you half that.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: Done!

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: peterman
line: Kramer, my friend,  consider Elaine at your disposal.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: Okay..  Well, I, Uh.. I like to work in the evenings..

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: elaine
line: Would you please just get on with the stupid Bob Saccamano story?!

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: Well, I'm on the phone with Bob, and I realize right then and there that I need to return this pair of pants. So, I'm off to the store.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: elaine
line: What happened to Bob Saccamano?

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: Well, nothing. His part of the story is done.  So I'm waiting for the subway, It's not coming, so I decided to hoof it through the tunnel.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: elaine
line: Alright, well, now that's something..

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: Well, I don't know if I lost track of time - or what, but the next think I knew..

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: elaine
line: A train is bearing down on you?!

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: No, I slipped - and fell in the mud. Ruining the very pants I was about to return.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: elaine
line: I don't understand.. you were wearing the pants you were returning?

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: Well, I guess I was..

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: elaine
line: What were you gonna wear on the way back?

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: Elaine, are you listening?! I didn't even get there!  All right, next story..

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: elaine
line: Alright, I think I got enough for one day.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah, yeah, chew on that.

speaker: elaine
line: Yeah, I'll chew on that.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, hey, listen, by the way - I'm hosting a little get-together tonight in honor of my little financial upturn..

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: elaine
line: Oh, thanks. I've got plans.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: Elaine, you should be there to document it.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: elaine
line: Oh, you're getting together with some of your jackass friends, and you want me to take notes?

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah, but get there after nine. You know, give the poeple a chance to loosen up.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: jerry
line: So you're denying him the scholarship just because he wants to be a city planner?

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: george
line: I was betrayed! That kid was like a son to me. And if there's one person you should be able to hold down, it's your own flesh and blood. Like my father.. my father's father before him.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: jerry
line: You know, maybe philanthropy is not your field.  Hello. Oh, Hi, Ellen. Yeah, I called the hotel.. we're all set for the weekend.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: george
line: You're spending the weekend with Ellen?

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: jerry
line: Vermont!  With any luck, they said we could stay an extra couple of days if we want to!  Four days at a beautiful bed-and-breakfast! I can't wait.. buy-bye.  What?  What is this?

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: george
line: You want to start?

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: Uh, No, no, no.. you go ahead. I gotta get my thoughts together.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: george
line: Jerry, this whole Ellen situation.. has gone far enough.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: jerry
line: What?!

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: Jerry, she's a loser.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: jerry
line: Where is this coming from? She's great!

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: george
line: Why're you doing this, Jerry? Is it your career? Things will pick up.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: jerry
line: There's nothing wrong with my career!

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: Well, I still like the Bloomingdale's executive training program for him.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: george
line: I though we said we weren't going to discuss that now!

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: Well, you know, I think it's something he should consider.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: george
line: Of course he should consider it, but now is not the time!

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: Listen, George, all these issues are interrelated.

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: jerry
line: Alright! Excuse me!  I'm not buying any of this!

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: All right, so what're you saying? That we're wrong? Oh, everybody's wrong but you!

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: jerry
line: You know, this is liek that Twilight Zone where the guy wakes up, and he's the same - but everyone else is different!

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys
speaker: kramer
line: Which one?

title: The_Van_Buren_Boys

speaker: elaine
line: What are you doing here?

title: The_Strike
speaker: kramer
line: I told them I was just about to see you.. It's a Festivus miracle!

title: The_Strike
speaker: estelle
line: Dinner's ready!

title: The_Strike
speaker: frank
line: Let's begin.

title: The_Strike
speaker: kramer
line: Uh.. that's right.

title: The_Strike
speaker: frank
line: Welcome, new comers. The tradition of Festivus begins with the airing of grievances. I got a lot of problems with you people! And now you're gonna hear about it! You, Kruger. My son tells me your company stinks!

title: The_Strike
speaker: george
line: Oh, God.

title: The_Strike
speaker: frank
line: Quiet, you'll get yours in a minute. Kruger, you couldn't smooth a silk sheet if you had a hot date with a babe.. I lost my train of thought.

title: The_Strike
speaker: jerry
line: Gwen! How'd you know I was here?

title: The_Strike
speaker: kramer
line: Another Festivus miracle!

title: The_Strike
speaker: elaine
line: Hey, I was in a shvitz for 6 hours. Give me a break.

title: The_Strike
speaker: jerry
line: Gwen. Gwen, wait! Ah!  Bad lighting on the porch.

title: The_Strike
speaker: elaine
line: Hey, how'd my horse do?

title: The_Strike
speaker: frank
line: And now as Festivus rolls on, we come to the feats of strength.

title: The_Strike
speaker: george
line: Not the feats of strength..

title: The_Strike
speaker: frank
line: This year, the honor goes to Mr. Kramer.

title: The_Strike
speaker: kramer
line: Uh-oh. Oh, gee, Frank, I'm sorry. I gotta go. I have to work a double shift at H&H.

title: The_Strike
speaker: jerry
line: I thought you were on strike?

title: The_Strike
speaker: kramer
line: Well, I caved. I mean, I really had to use their bathroom. Frank, no offence, but this holiday is a little  out there.

title: The_Strike
speaker: george
line: Kramer! You can't go! Who's gonna do the feats of strength?

title: The_Strike
speaker: frank
line: Good thinking, Kruger. Until you pin me, George, Festivus is not over!

title: The_Strike
speaker: george
line: Oh, please, somebody, stop this!

title: The_Strike
speaker: frank
line: Let's rumble!

title: The_Strike
speaker: estelle
line: I think you can take him, Georgie!

title: The_Strike
speaker: george
line: Oh, come on! Be sensible.

title: The_Strike
speaker: frank
line: Stop crying, and fight your father!

title: The_Strike
speaker: george
line: Ow! .. Ow! I give, I give! Uncle!

title: The_Strike
speaker: frank
line: This is the best Festivus ever!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: When are they gonna have the flying cars, already?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Yeah, they have been promising that for a while..

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Years. When we were kids, they made it seem like it was right around the corner.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: I think Ed Begley Jr. has one.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: No. That's just electric.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: What about Harrison Ford? He had one in, uh, Blade Runner. That was a cool one.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: What's the competition, Chitty Chitty Bang Bang?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Well, what do you think the big holdup is?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: The government is very touchy about us being in the air. Let us run around on the ground as much as we want. Anything in the air is a big production.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Yeah, right. And what about the floating cities?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: And the underwater bubble cities?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: It's like we're living in the '50s here.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: It's good suspension!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Would you stop it? You'll have plenty of time to destroy it after I get it. Hey, George, I'm buyin' this car.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Shhh… What is wrong with you? You never tell 'em you like the car.  You're not sure what you want. You don't even know why you're here.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: You're getting that vein again.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: I'm starving. We should have had lunch first..

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: It'll be twenty minutes. I told ya, Puddy's getting me an insider deal.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Since when is Elaine's boyfriend selling cars? I thought he was a mechanic.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: I guess he graduated.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: There's an easy move: go from screwin' you behind your back to screwin' you right to your face.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Thank you.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Puddy's just gonna give you the car, huh?  You'll see. First they stick you with the undercoating, rust-proofing, dealer prep. Suddenly, you're on your back like a turtle.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: All right. Calm down.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: My father had a car salesman buddy. He was gonna fix him up real nice. Next thing I know, I'm gettin' dropped of in a Le Car with a fabric sunroof. All the kids are shoutin' at me, "Hey, Le George! Bonjour, Le George! Let's stuff Le George in Le Locker!"

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: Jerry, I don't think this thing is hooked up right.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: All right, we're goin' in.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: Uh, borrow. It's for my friend. Yeah, he'll be buying..

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, I don't think so. No, he's an entertainer. You know, all over the place. That's where I come in.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah, neighbor. That's right. Yeah, why don't we take this boiler out for a shakedown huh?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Hold it! One more step and we're walkin'!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: George.  Sorry, we're just waiting for David Puddy.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: He is. You don't know what I'm doin' here.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: Hey.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Hey.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: Sorry I'm late.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: My new salesman boyfriend took me out to celebrate his promotion.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Ah. Where'd you go?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: Uh, to a restaurant.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: Arby's.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: I had the roast beef…

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: So, Puddy, I decided I'm gonna go with another 900 convertible.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: All right. Classic.  High-five.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: David, can you tell me where the Xerox machine is?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: Oh, sure, babe. Salesman-only copy room  right there.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: Oh.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: Hey, come on, guys. I'll show you the 900.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Yeah, you show us the 900.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: No, no, no, I didn't.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: Well, it's a test drive, right? I never drive around here. If I'm gonna recommend this car, I need to see that it'll handle my daily routine.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: Just a little place I like to call, "You'll see".

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: I'm starving. You got any of those free donuts you use to soften people up?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: By the service department.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: All right, remember: no rust-proofing. Commit to nothing. If you have to speak - mumble.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Au revoir, Le George.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Don't think it can't happen!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: So, Puddy, this is a pretty good move for you, huh? No more "grease monkey".

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: I don't care for that term.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Oh. Sorry, I didn't know..

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: No, I don't know too many monkeys who could take apart a fuel injector.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: I saw one once that could do sign language.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: Yeah, I saw that one. Uh.. Koko.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Yeah, Koko.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: Right, Koko. That chimp's all right.  High-five.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Hey, hey, hey! What's goin' on here?  You didn't agree to anything, did ya?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: No. We both just saw the same monkey.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Well, I got screwed on the donuts. There were none left. Heh!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: Well, there's a vending machine. I could show you where it is.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Hey, gimme a dollar.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Where's your money?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: I'm here helpin' you.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: Hey. Where's Puddy? The copy machine is broken.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Heh, heh, heh. That's what they want you to think.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Hey, Elaine, have you noticed your boyfriend has developed an annoying little habit?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: The squinting?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: No.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: The staring?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: No. He keeps asking me to give him a high-five.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: I thought all guys do that.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Slapping hands is the lowest form of male primate ritual. In fact, even some of them have moved on - they're doing sign language now.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: It's that bad?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: What do you think the Nazis were doin'?  That was the heil-five.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: Isn't that from your act, like, ten years ago?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: It was a good bit in the '80's, and it's still relatable today.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: Good news. We got a 900 in black. That's the hot color.  High-five.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: Um, David, you know what? Can you come help me fix the copy machine? Come.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: You owe me five.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Twix..  B-5.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Ah, come on!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Ah, excuse me. Do you have, uh, change of a dollar?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Could I, uh, could I trade you for another dollar?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Ah, excuse me. When your, uh, when your wallet was open, I - I glanced inside, and I couldn't help but notice that you have several crisp dollar bills.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Perhaps you could look again, please? I'm very hungry.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: I guess everyone here enjoys giving the old screwgie, huh?! You're all doin' a hell of a job!  Ho, ho. What I would do with you..

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: I think the candy comes out over there.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: People can drop change down here, Jerry. And they're too lazy to pick it up.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Either that, or they've got a weird little hang-up about lying face-down in filth. Why don't you just go to the cashier?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: The cashier is at lunch - which is where I'd like to be.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: How much was under there?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: I think somethin' bit me. I just need another nickel.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Hey, Puddy thinks I should go for the CD player. What do you think?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Ho, ho, ho! He's got a live one. He's just reeling his big fish in!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Hey, can I have my dollar back?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: It's wrinkled. It's worthless.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Ha, ha, ha, ha!  Come on! Jump!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: man
line: They just put out some more donuts.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: They did?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: man
line: Last one.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: Well, just one more errand and we can head back.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: Oh? Well, how much gas do you think is in there right now?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: You know, Rick, oftentimes, Jerry - he lends me his car and I find myself in a situation where the car is almost out of gas. But, for a variety of reasons, I don't want to be the one responsible for purchasing costly gasoline.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: Well, I make it up to him in other ways.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: As you will see, the candy bar is paid for, and yet, remains dangling in the machine.  Hey, it's gone. Where is my Twix?  What?! That guy's eatin' it!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Uh, it was dangling! There were only two left in the machine! He must've bought one, and gotten both.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: No!  Hey! Hey! I see you! That is my Twix!  Oh, ha, ha! Ho, ho!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: Paper jam.. Got it!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: Yay!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: High-five.  On the flip side.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: David, um, I..

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: Don't leave me hangin'.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: You're a salesman now - and the high-five is… it's very "grease monkey."

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: What did I tell you about that?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: Ah, I, I'm sorry, but the high-five is just so stupid.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: Oh yeah? I'll tell you what's stupid. You. Stupid.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: Oh, that is really mature.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: Yeah? So are you. You're the grease monkey.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: Uh… that doesn't make any sense. I am leaving.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: Yeah, if you leave, we're through.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: Fine! We're through!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: Oh, so you're leaving?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: That's right.  High-five!  On the flip side!  Takin' me to Arby's…

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Hey! Wh-where are you…?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: Let's finish this up.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Did you two break up?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: That chick's whacked. We're history.  I just left out a couple of things: uh, rust-proofing…

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: "Rust-proofing"?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: Transport charge, storage surcharge, additional overcharge, finder's fee…

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: "Finder's fee"? It was on the lot!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: Yeah, that's right.  Uh, floor mats, keys…

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: "Keys"?!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: How ya gonna start it?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Excuse me. I believe you just ate my Twix bar. It was dangling. And when you purchased your Twix bar, you got a little freebie, and you never bothered to ask why, or seek out its rightful owner.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Huh. You must think I'm pretty stupid.  That was no 5th Avenue bar. I can see the crumb right there in the corner of your lip! Now, that-that-that is a cookie - and we all know that Twix is the only candy bar with the cookie crunch.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Nougat? Please. I think I've reached the point in my life where I can tell the difference between nougat and cookie. So let's not just say things that we both know are obvious fabrications.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: I know about the vein! I can't believe this guy..

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Hey, George!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Hey, starving!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: No, last one. Listen, you gotta help me out. Elaine and Puddy just broke up, he's treatin' me just like a regular customer, now!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: I tried to tell you, but you wouldn't listen. No, ho, ho! You were gonna get a deal, huh? There's no laws in this place. Anything goes! It's Thunderdome!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: There's still some overlap between the needle and the slash below the "E".

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, I've been in the slash many times. This is nothing. You'll get used to it. Just,  put it out of your mind.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: Well, I almost did once, and I blacked out. When I came to, the car was in a ditch, and the tank was full. I don't know who did it, and I never got to thank them..

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: Whoop! Whoop!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: So, listen, Puddy. When we first started this deal, I thought things were gonna be different. Now, if you want to play hard ball, I got my friend, George, here, and he can play pretty hard… ball.  George, vein it up.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: All right, Puddy, listen, and listen good: I need to know the name of that mechanic that walks around here. Big guy, a liar. Short name. Sam? Moe? Sol?!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: George! Can we focus on the car, here?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: I'm starving! I can feel my stomach sucking up against my spine.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: Jerry, I just need your signature here, and we'll get you that yellow car ready to go.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Yellow? I wanted black.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: I can't give you black at that price.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: George, would you help me, please?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Yes. This is wrong!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Sing it, sister!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Just because a candy bar fails to fall from its perch…

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Oh, God…

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: …does not imply transfer of ownership. Moe, Sol, or… Lem is not gonna get away with this!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: I'll be right back.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: puddy
line: Okay.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Hey, George!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: No, Sir. We are down there.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: All right, I'm satisfied. We better get some gas.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: What do you mean?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: There was no plan.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: What, they drove to a dealership?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: You are one sick mama… I like it.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: kramer
line: Yup! Yup!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: Hello?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Elaine, you've got to get back down to the dealer. Puddy is screwin' me on this car, which is yellow now!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: Who is this?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Elaine!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: What?!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: You gotta get back together with Puddy so I can make this deal.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: You know, just that you cared enough to call means so much, Jerry.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: You're gonna get back together, anyway. It's thousands of dollars!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: Oh, I don't know..

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Come on. Then you don't have to see him again 'til my 15,000-mile check.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: Well, will you pay my cab fare out there?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Fine.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: And I didn't like that roast beef, so how 'bout some lunch?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: No. No lunch.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: I'll hang this phone up right now!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: All right! Lunch!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: elaine
line: I'll see ya.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Bye.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: jerry
line: Everybody's ripping me off!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Yes, I'd like to report a problem with one of your mechanics.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Yeah, right… I'm gonna get my car repaired at a dealership. Huh! Why don't I just flush my money down the toilet?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: One of your guys - Kip, or Ned, short name - stole my Twix candy bar!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: He might as well have! I caught him, and his face was covered in chocolate and cookie crumbs.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Oh, it was. But he claimed it was a 5th Avenue bar.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Oh, no, no. Twix is the only candy with the cookie crunch.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: No. Rice and caramel.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: No.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: Please.

title: The_Dealership
speaker: woman
line: You know they changed the name from Hundred-Thousand-Dollar bar to Hundred-Grand?

title: The_Dealership
speaker: george
line: All I want is my seventy-five cents back, an apology, and for him to be fired!

title: The_Dealership
speaker: man
line: What's the one with the swirling chocolate in the commercial?

title: The_Dealership

line: Yes. There was this homeless guy who used to urinate on our garbage cans.

speaker: jerry
line: Good. How did you handle that?

speaker: elaine
line: Well, we gave him a few bucks, and... now he goes in the alley across the street.

speaker: jerry
line: Same situation. Pay him off, and you're clean.

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: elaine
line: Well, I am NOT paying Glenn off to get out of this relationship. Wh-what am I supposed to do, just walk into his hovel, and hand him... well, how much do you think it would be?

speaker: george
line: Hey.

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: jerry
line: Hey, where have you been?

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: george
line: Seeing Maura. Apparently, I was unable to break up beyond a reasonable doubt.

speaker: elaine
line: If only he could have been cheating on his wife, you know, things would have been so much simpler.

speaker: george
line: Who's this, Blue Arrow?

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: elaine
line: Green Lantern.

line: We found out his super power was lack of money.

speaker: elaine
line: All right.

speaker: jerry
line: He's invulnerable to creditors.

speaker: elaine
line: We get it.

speaker: elaine
line: Thank you.

speaker: george
line: Hey, Elaine. Maybe his girlfriend is Lois Loan.

speaker: elaine
line: Ooh,  well crafted.

speaker: george
line: Hey, maybe this cheating thing is what I could use to ditch Maura.

line: Sure, just tell Maura you're having an affair.

speaker: george
line: She's like a district attorney. If it's not the truth, I'll break under the cross. I actually have to do it.

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: jerry
line: ... Could you move over there?!

speaker: george
line: Hey, you know, there's this secretary at work that always had a crush on me.

speaker: jerry
line: Really? How come you never pursued her before?

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: george
line: She's too tanned. It's the middle of the winter, she's like a carrot.

speaker: elaine
line: Did I leave my glasses here?

speaker: jerry
line: He can wipe out his checking account in a single bounce!

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: elaine
line: Keep 'em!

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: kramer
line: Heh.

speaker: jerry
line: There's a giant parrot in the hallway.

speaker: kramer
line: It's Phil's.

speaker: jerry
line: Who?

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: kramer
line: Our neighbor that you... turned against.  Anyway, I told him it'd be fine with us if he wanted to let it stretch its wings out in the hallway.

speaker: jerry
line: What'd ya tell him that for?

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: kramer
line: Because since you've been playing God with the front door, I've been tryin' to smooth things out, Jerry. In fact, I was just hanging out at his place.

speaker: jerry
line: Really? What's it like? Is it nicer than mine? Where does he have the couch?

speaker: jerry
line: He let you?

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: kramer
line: No, he doesn't know. See, I hid it without tellin' him. So, uh,  Phil won't be compulsively looking for it like some people... You!

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: george
line: So, you... you say you've been in the city all winter?

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: george
line: Well...  heeere we are

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: george
line: Ho ho!

speaker: george
line: Are you sure? 'Cause it could really help me out of a jam.

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: george
line: Oh, not more building.

speaker: george
line: No?

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: george
line: All right.

speaker: elaine
line: So, uh, what are we doing in this alley, anyway?

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: elaine
line: Oh.

speaker: elaine
line: What are you doing? What is that?

speaker: elaine
line: It's garbage.

speaker: elaine
line: All right, that's it.  How do you spell your last name?

line: I'll make it out to cash. How 'bout two hundred bucks? Two-fifty?

speaker: elaine
line: Make it three hundred.

speaker: elaine
line: Aw, Glenn.

speaker: jerry
line: Hi. Is Phil here?
