speaker: jerry
line: Phil... hi. I-I know we got off to kind of a bad start. But your bird, which is lovely... by the way, made a mess on my door.

speaker: jerry
line: I thought maybe you'd clean it up, or your maid, there.

speaker: jerry
line: All right, I think we're done here.

speaker: jerry
line: So, you're in a relationship with a woman you don't like, and you're having an affair with a woman that won't have sex with you.

speaker: george
line: This isn't going well.

speaker: jerry
line: I cannot find my Jerry Lewis cufflinks. Without 'em, I have no in!

line: You don't need the cufflinks! You have the same name!  'Jerry'!

speaker: jerry
line: Where are you goin'? Help me look!

speaker: george
line: It's a big night. I'm, uh, ice skating with one, and going to a staged reading of "Godspell" with the other.

speaker: jerry
line: Which is with who?

speaker: george
line: It doesn't matter.

speaker: kramer
line: Whoo! Boy. Yeah, you clean up nice.

speaker: jerry
line: I can't go until I find my cufflinks.

line: Yeah, see? I knew you would lose 'em. That's why I took 'em out of your dresser drawer and put 'em in my strongbox.

speaker: kramer
line: Yeah. Just give it to the Portuguese guy, and he... puts it in the incinerator.

speaker: jerry
line: Just get the key and let's get out of here.

speaker: kramer
line: Yeah, yeah.  You know, it's a... it's a funny thing about that bird dying. I hid the key in Fredo's food dish. Whoo! That's a weeeird coincidence.

speaker: jerry
line: Kramer!?

speaker: kramer

speaker: jerry
line: Kramer, I need those cufflinks, but now they're in the box, and the key is in the bird... What are we gonna do?

speaker: jerry
line: Oh, no!

speaker: kramer
line: I'll get the shovel.

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: george
line: The, uh, actor that played Jesus made some odd choices.

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: george
line: I mean, uh... I had fun ice skating.

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: george
line: Maura.  Oh, my God! What are you doing here?!

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: george
line: Uhh! I'm caught in my own web of lies!

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: george
line: This is all blowing up in my face! My serious girlfriend, and my torrid love affair have accidentally crossed paths. I have ruined three lives...  Well, I understand if you never want to see me again, so...

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: george
line: What? So, this is still not over?

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: george
line: You?

title: The_Strongbox
speaker: george
line: All right.

speaker: elaine
line: Yeah, and I got you a cord of wood, so you won't have to burn 'em.

speaker: elaine
line: Who is this?

line: So, what are you gonna do? Are you gonna live here, or are you gonna move out, or what?

line: Oh. Well, would you look at that.  I guess I forgot to lock it.

speaker: jerry
line: You mean it was open? We desecrated a pet cemetery for nothing?

speaker: kramer
line: Well, this is one for the books, huh, Jerry?... Reeeally one for the books!

title: The_Wizard

line: When are they gonna learn that any news about China is an instant page-turner?  What's that?

speaker: jerry
line: Ah, I'll tell him I got it on the street, and maybe it's hot. That's his favorite.

line: At the funeral, give or take. You know, deep down, I always kinda felt that they blamed me for Susan's death.

speaker: george
line: Rosses.

speaker: george
line: Well, sorry I missed that, uh, charity thing. But this was one of those truly glorious Hampton weekends that you always hear about.

speaker: george
line: Yeah, I may move out there.  I mean it, I'll do it! OK, I'll see ya later. Keep it real!

line: All right, I'll see you guys.

line: Yeah.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: kramer
line: Morty, what're you lookin' at?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: morty
line: I'll tell you what I'm looking at: the next condo president of Del Boca Vista, Phase Three.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: kramer
line: Hmm.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah, yeah. Forget about all that. First thing is first. Warranty information. Name, we know that. Uh, hobbies. Skiing, racquetball...

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: It doesn't matter, it doesn't matter, it doesn't matter. Um. Oh, here's one: race.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: It certainly should be. It's nobody's damn business! But they really would like to know.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: What?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: laughing awkwardly: Oh. Right. Good one.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: Really?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: No, but... it is very nice to know.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: So did you figure out Darryl's... you know.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: Ah, I've given up. So, now we're going to a bunch of Spanish restaurants. I figure that'll cover us either way.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: You're a master of race relations.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: Hey, so Kramer's running for president of the condo?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: Yeah, it's all my father's doing.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: He wants to install Kramer in a puppet regime and then wield power from behind the scenes. Preferably from the sauna in the clubhouse.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: Oh, heh heh heh. Who are they running against?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: Common sense and a guy in a wheelchair.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: Jerry?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: He's still down with his folks.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: What are you doin' here?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: (overhearing the other two: Elaine, Elaine--

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: I'm gettin' his mail.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: Oh, no.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: He asked you to get the mail?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: Mm-hmm.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: Jerry, why is Elaine getting your mail?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: George, listen to me. I have a very important job for you. I want you to come by twice a day and flush the toilet so the gaskets don't dry out and leak.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: What?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: What about the mail?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: This is far more important. You must exercise the gaskets, George.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: All right, Jerry. I'll do it. See ya.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: So, I ran into the Rosses again.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: Oh, right, at the coffee shop. Where did they get the idea that you have a place in the Hamptons?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: From me.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: What did you say?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: I told them I have a place in the Hamptons. What did you say?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: I told them you didn't. And I laughed and I laughed.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: So, they knew? Those liars!

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: But you lied first.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: Yeah, but they let me go on and on all about the Hamptons, they never said a thing! You don't let somebody lie when they know you're lying. You call them a liar!

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: Like you're a liar!

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: Yes. Thank you! Is that so hard?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: So, this is over, not over? I'm bettin', not over.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: Hmm-hmm, not by a long shot. I'm calling up the Rosses and inviting them up to my non-existent place in the Hamptons. Then we'll see who blinks first.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: Haven't you done enough to these people?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: This is not about them. Now, if you'll excuse me, I have to exercise Jerry's gaskets.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: kramer
line: Vote for Kramer.  Cosmo Kramer. I'm running for condo president. I'd like your vote. Thanks.  Remember, ma'am, a vote for me, is a vote for Kramer.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: kramer
line: Gladly.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: What?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: Interracial? Us?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: Yes, it's awful! They're upset because we're an interracial couple. That is racism!

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: Me neither. Well, maybe this turkey club.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: So... here I am. Ready to take you to the Hamptons.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: Do you have your bathing suits?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: Speak now, or we are headed to the Hamptons. It's a two-hour drive. Once you get in that car, we are going all the way... to the Hamptons. All right, you wanna get nuts? Come on. Let's get nuts!

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: Hey, Dad. You know you can program this thing to beep every time you need to take a vitamin.  Dad, you look so different.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, no. We're campaigning, Jerry. To rule the people, one... must walk among them.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: morty
line: This is the home stretch. Tomorrow's the election!

title: The_Wizard
speaker: kramer
line: Right. Yeah. The polls close after dinner, three o'clock. But then when we win, the celebration goes all night until the break of eight p.m.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: You know, you can put that whole schedule right in your daily planner.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: morty
line: Daily what?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: helen
line: Have you read today's Boca Breeze?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: kramer
line: Hey, look at that. Picture of me, huh?  Candidate Cosmo Kramer caught barefoot in clubhouse.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: morty
line: Barefoot in the clubhouse? Don't you realize this is against the rules.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: kramer
line: Well, I couldn't find my shoes.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: Kramer, these people work and wait their whole lives to move down here, sit in the heat, pretend it's not hot, and enforce these rules.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: helen
line: Who wants hot chocolate?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, yeah! Me.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: morty
line: This is a huge scandal! We need damage control.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: kramer
line: All right, look. People seem to like those tip calculators, huh?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: Wizards!

title: The_Wizard
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah, well, how 'bout if we give one out to every member on the condo board.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: Kramer...

title: The_Wizard
speaker: morty
line: There are twenty people on the board. Thank God you can get that deal.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: kramer
line: Payoffs. Now we're playin' politics. All right, what do we next, Morty, huh? Wiretaps, slush funds?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: morty
line: First, I need a nap.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: helen
line: Oh, I'll get your electric blanket!

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: Kramer, I can't get that many Wizards.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: kramer
line: Well, what about your deal, huh?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: I didn't have a deal! They're two hundred dollars a pop. What do I do?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: kramer
line: Well, don't worry about it. I know a guy.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: Down here?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: kramer
line: Yeah, Bob Saccamano's father.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: You want to hear more? The master bedroom opens into the solarium.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: Yes, two solariums. Quite a find. And I have horses, too?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: Snoopy and Prickly Pete. Should I keep driving?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: Housewarming gift.  All right, we're taking it up a notch!

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: Long day?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: I hear ya, Sister.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah. It's OK. My boyfriend's black. Here he is. See?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: Hey.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: Aren't you?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: You're black. You said we were an interracial couple.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: I am?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: No. Why would you think that?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: That's because I thought you were black.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: I don't think we should be talking about this.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: I'm white.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: I guess.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: elaine
line: Yeah. So do you want to go to the Gap?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: kramer
line: Oh, well... I handed out all the Wizards. Polls close in one hour. Whoo hoo hoo! I think we've got this baby all sewn up, huh? Oh, uh, there was an extra one. Norman Burgerman, he won't be leavin' any tips where he is.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: Aw.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: morty
line: Congratulations, Mr. President.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: kramer
line: Congratulations, Mr. Puppet Master.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: morty
line: What are you talking about?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: morty
line: This isn't a Wizard, it's a Willard.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: A Willard? Saccamano, Sr. screwed me!

title: The_Wizard
speaker: morty
line: Jerry, why didn't you get them Wizards?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: Because a real Wizard's two hundred dollars.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: morty
line: You didn't have a deal?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: No deal. Not hot.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: kramer
line: What?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: kramer
line: Well, the people have spoken. Well, that's it for me. I'm, I'm headin' back to New York.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: Dad, I'm sorry.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: morty
line: You should be! How could you spend two hundred dollars on a tip calculator?!

title: The_Wizard
speaker: jerry
line: It does other things!

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: Almost there.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: We, uh, we go on foot from here.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: There's no house! It's a lie! There's no solarium. There's no Prickly Pete. There's no other solarium.

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: Then, why? Why did you make me drive all the way out here? Why didn't you say something? Why? Why? Why?

title: The_Wizard
speaker: george
line: Oh.

line: Alright, be careful with the car, babe.

speaker: elaine
line: Yeah, yeah.

line: And don't move the seat, I got it right where I like it.

line: Don't peel out.

speaker: elaine
line: I won't.

speaker: george
line: Well, I know when I'm a little strapped, I sometimes drop off my rent check having forgotten to sign it. That could buy us some time.

title: The_Burning
speaker: george
line: Or we don't even send the check and then when they call, we pretend we're the cleaning service. Heh heh. "Hello? I sorry, no here Kruger."

speaker: george
line: I had 'em, Jerry. They loved me.

speaker: jerry
line: And then?

title: The_Burning
speaker: george
line: I lost them. I can usually come up with one good comment during a meeting but by the end it's buried under a pile of gaffs and bad puns.

title: The_Burning
speaker: jerry
line: Showmanship, George. When you hit that high note, you say goodnight and walk off.

title: The_Burning
speaker: george
line: I can't just leave.

title: The_Burning
speaker: jerry
line: That's the way they do it in Vegas.

speaker: george
line: You never played Vegas.

speaker: jerry
line: I hear things.

title: The_Burning
speaker: elaine
line: Here's one. I borrowed Puddy's car and all the presets on his radio were Christian rock stations.

title: The_Burning
speaker: george
line: I like Christian rock. It's very positive. It's not like those real musicians who think they're so cool and hip.

title: The_Burning
speaker: elaine
line: So, you think that Puddy actually believes in something?

title: The_Burning
speaker: jerry
line: It's a used car, he probably never changed the presets.

title: The_Burning
speaker: elaine
line: Yes, he is lazy.

title: The_Burning
speaker: jerry
line: Plus he probably doesn't even know how to program the buttons.

title: The_Burning
speaker: elaine
line: Yes, he is dumb.

title: The_Burning
speaker: jerry
line: So you prefer dumb and lazy to religious?

title: The_Burning
speaker: elaine
line: Dumb and lazy, I understand.

title: The_Burning
speaker: george
line: Tell you how you could check.

title: The_Burning
speaker: elaine
line: How?

title: The_Burning
speaker: george
line: Reprogram all the buttons, see if he changes them back. You know? The old switcheroo.

title: The_Burning
speaker: jerry
line: No, no, the old switcheroo is you poison your drink then you switch it with the other person's.

title: The_Burning
speaker: george
line: No, it's doing the same thing to someone that they did to you.

title: The_Burning
speaker: jerry
line: Yeah, Elaine's gonna do the same thing to Puddy's radio that the radio did to her.

title: The_Burning
speaker: george
line: Well that's the gist of it!

speaker: elaine
line: Quiet! So where is this Sophie?

line: Oh, she's picking me up in a few minutes.

line: How long have you two been together?

speaker: jerry
line: I dunno. Since the last one. Oh, here she is. You wanna meet her?

speaker: elaine
line: Nah.

speaker: george
line: Nah.

line: By the way, how did Puddy get back in the picture?

line: I needed to move a bureau.

line: Aah-choo.

line: A little wetter. See, I didn't believe it.

line: Yeah, we're going down to Mt. Sinai Hospital, See they hire actors to help the students practice diagnosing.

line: Well the better ones. Alright, let's practice retching.

line: HUAAHHH!!

line: HUAAHHH!!

line: HUAAHHH!!

line: HUAAHHH!!

line: Would you hold it a second?! Thank you, will you get out of here with that stuff?

line: Mickey, DTs.

line: Sorry buddy, this is the "Hamlet" of diseases. Severe pain, nausea, delusions, it's got everything.

line: Howbout you, do you wanna trade?

speaker: man
line: Sure.

line: Okay, what do you got?

line: The surgeon left a sponge inside me.

line: Good luck with that.

line: I knew I had hit my high note so I thanked the crowd and I was gone.

line: What did you do the rest of the day?

speaker: george
line: I saw "Titanic". So that old woman, she's just a liar, right?

speaker: jerry
line: And a bit of a tramp if you ask me.

speaker: elaine
line: Hello boys.

line: Well yeah, I got him because he seemed so one-dimensional, I feel misled.

line: I think it's neat. You don't hear that much about god anymore.

speaker: jerry
line: I hear things. Hey, so Sophie gave me the "It's me" on the phone today.

line: "It's me?" Isn't it a little premature?

line: I thought so.

speaker: elaine
line: Hah. She's not a "me". I'm a "me".

speaker: george
line: I'm against all "it's me"s. So self-absorbed and egotistical, it's like those hip musicians with their complicated shoes!

speaker: kramer
line: Well, I got gonorrhea.

speaker: elaine
line: That seems about right.

line: That's what they gave me.

speaker: jerry
line: No, no. He's pretending he's got gonorrhea so med students can diagnose it.

speaker: kramer
line: And it's a waste of my talent. It's just a little burning. Mickey, he got bacterial meningitis.

title: The_Burning

line: I guess there are no small diseases, only small actors.

speaker: george
line: Alright that's it for me. Good night everybody.

line: What was that?

line: Showmanship, George is trying to get out on a high note.

line: See, showmanship. Maybe that's what my gonorrhea is missing.

speaker: jerry
line: Yes! Step into that spotlight and belt that gonorrhea out to the back row.

speaker: kramer
line: Yes, yes I will! I'm gonna make people feel my gonorrhea, and feel the gonorrhea themselves.

line: Just a little burning during urination.

title: The_Burning
speaker: kramer
line: The haunting memories of lost love. May I?  Lights?  Our eyes met across the crowded hat store. I, a customer, and she a coquettish haberdasher. Oh, I pursued and she withdrew, then she pursued and I withdrew, and so we danced. I burned for her, much like the burning during urination that I would experience soon afterwards.

speaker: kramer
line: Gonorrhea!

line: One message. Hope it's not from you.

line: Alright, I'll tell you what you do. You call her back and give her the "it's me", heh? Pull the old switcheroo.

line: I think that's a "what's good for the goose is good for the gander".

line: It's a goose that's had the old switcheroo pulled on it. Hi Sophie, it's me.

line: Good, let her think it.

line: So, what's going on?

line: Ask about you, ask about you.

line: Right, right, the tractor story.

line: Yeah I better get to a doctor, bye.  That was close! What drives me to take chances like that?

speaker: george
line: That was very real.

speaker: jerry
line: She said there's some tractor story that she hasn't told me about.

line: Woah, back it up, back it up. Beep, beep, beep. Tractor story?

line: Beep, beep, beep? What are you doing?

line: So where do you wanna eat?
